98namespace Catch {

103 class StringRef {
104 public:
105 using size_type = std::size_t;
106 using const_iterator = const char*;
107
108 private:
109 static constexpr char const* const s_empty = "";
110
111 char const* m_start = s_empty;
112 size_type m_size = 0;
113
114 public: // construction
115 constexpr StringRef() noexcept = default;
116
117 StringRef( char const* rawChars ) noexcept;
118
119 constexpr StringRef( char const* rawChars, size_type size ) noexcept
120 : m_start( rawChars ),
121 m_size( size )
122 {}
123
124 StringRef( std::string const& stdString ) noexcept
125 : m_start( stdString.c_str() ),
126 m_size( stdString.size() )
127 {}
128
129 explicit operator std::string() const {
130 return std::string(m_start, m_size);
131 }
132
133 public: // operators
134 auto operator == ( StringRef other ) const noexcept -> bool;
135 auto operator != (StringRef other) const noexcept -> bool {
136 return !(*this == other);
137 }
138
139 constexpr auto operator[] ( size_type index ) const noexcept -> char {
140 assert(index < m_size);
141 return m_start[index];
142 }
143
144 bool operator<(StringRef rhs) const noexcept;
145
146 public: // named queries
147 constexpr auto empty() const noexcept -> bool {
148 return m_size == 0;
149 }
150 constexpr auto size() const noexcept -> size_type {
151 return m_size;
152 }
153
154 // Returns a substring of [start, start + length).
155 // If start + length > size(), then the substring is [start, start + size()).
156 // If start > size(), then the substring is empty.
157 constexpr StringRef substr(size_type start, size_type length) const noexcept {
158 if (start < m_size) {
159 const auto shortened_size = m_size - start;
160 return StringRef(m_start + start, (shortened_size < length) ? shortened_size : length);
161 } else {
162 return StringRef();
163 }
164 }
165
166 // Returns the current start pointer. May not be null-terminated.
167 constexpr char const* data() const noexcept {
168 return m_start;
169 }
170
171 constexpr const_iterator begin() const { return m_start; }
172 constexpr const_iterator end() const { return m_start + m_size; }
173
174
175 friend std::string& operator += (std::string& lhs, StringRef sr);
176 friend std::ostream& operator << (std::ostream& os, StringRef sr);
177 friend std::string operator+(StringRef lhs, StringRef rhs);
178
185 int compare( StringRef rhs ) const;
186 };
187
188
189 constexpr auto operator ""_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> StringRef {
190 return StringRef( rawChars, size );
191 }
192} // namespace Catch
193
194constexpr auto operator ""_catch_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> Catch::StringRef {
195 return Catch::StringRef( rawChars, size );
196}
197
198#endif // CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED

289#ifndef CATCH_COMPILER_CAPABILITIES_HPP_INCLUDED

292// Detect a number of compiler features - by compiler
293// The following features are defined:
294//
295// CATCH_CONFIG_WINDOWS_SEH : is Windows SEH supported?
296// CATCH_CONFIG_POSIX_SIGNALS : are POSIX signals supported?
297// CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS : Are exceptions enabled?
298// ****************
299// Note to maintainers: if new toggles are added please document them
300// in configuration.md, too
301// ****************
302
303// In general each macro has a _NO_<feature name> form
304// (e.g. CATCH_CONFIG_NO_POSIX_SIGNALS) which disables the feature.
305// Many features, at point of detection, define an _INTERNAL_ macro, so they
306// can be combined, en-mass, with the _NO_ forms later.
307
308
309

320# elif (defined(TARGET_OS_IPHONE) && TARGET_OS_IPHONE == 1)

322# endif
323
324#elif defined(linux) || defined(__linux) || defined(__linux__)
325# define CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX
326
327#elif defined(WIN32) || defined(__WIN32__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__MINGW32__)
328# define CATCH_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
329
330# if defined( WINAPI_FAMILY ) && ( WINAPI_FAMILY == WINAPI_FAMILY_APP )
331# define CATCH_PLATFORM_WINDOWS_UWP
332# endif

334#elif defined(__ORBIS__) || defined(__PROSPERO__)
335# define CATCH_PLATFORM_PLAYSTATION
336
337#endif

339#endif // CATCH_PLATFORM_HPP_INCLUDED

353// Only GCC compiler should be used in this block, so other compilers trying to
354// mask themselves as GCC should be ignored.
355#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && !defined(__ICC) && !defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined(__LCC__)
356# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic push" )
357# define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic pop" )
358
359// This only works on GCC 9+. so we have to also add a global suppression of Wparentheses
360// for older versions of GCC.
361# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
362 _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )
363
364# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
365 _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-variable\"" )
366
367# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
368 _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wuseless-cast\"" )
369
370# define CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(...) (void)__builtin_constant_p(__VA_ARGS__)
371
372#endif
373
374#if defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined(__clang__)
375# ifdef __NVCC_DIAG_PRAGMA_SUPPORT__
376// New pragmas introduced in CUDA 11.5+
377# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "nv_diagnostic push" )
378# define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "nv_diagnostic pop" )
379# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS _Pragma( "nv_diag_suppress 177" )
380# else
381# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS _Pragma( "diag_suppress 177" )
382# endif
383#endif

385// clang-cl defines _MSC_VER as well as __clang__, which could cause the
386// start/stop internal suppression macros to be double defined.
387#if defined(__clang__) && !defined(_MSC_VER)
388
389# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic push" )
390# define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic pop" )
391
392#endif // __clang__ && !_MSC_VER
393
394#if defined(__clang__)
395
396// As of this writing, IBM XL's implementation of __builtin_constant_p has a bug
397// which results in calls to destructors being emitted for each temporary,
398// without a matching initialization. In practice, this can result in something
399// like `std::string::~string` being called on an uninitialized value.
400//
401// For example, this code will likely segfault under IBM XL:
402// ```
403// REQUIRE(std::string("12") + "34" == "1234")
404// ```
405//
406// Similarly, NVHPC's implementation of `__builtin_constant_p` has a bug which
407// results in calls to the immediately evaluated lambda expressions to be
408// reported as unevaluated lambdas.
409// https://developer.nvidia.com/nvidia_bug/3321845.
410//
411// Therefore, `CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN` is not implemented.
412# if !defined(__ibmxl__) && !defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined( __NVCOMPILER )
413# define CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(...) (void)__builtin_constant_p(__VA_ARGS__) /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg, hicpp-vararg) */
414# endif
415
416
417# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
418 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wexit-time-destructors\"" ) \
419 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wglobal-constructors\"")
420
421# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
422 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )
423
424# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
425 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-variable\"" )
426
427# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \
428 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wgnu-zero-variadic-macro-arguments\"" )
429
430# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_WARNINGS \
431 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-template\"" )
432
433# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_COMMA_WARNINGS \
434 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wcomma\"" )
435
436#endif // __clang__

920#ifndef CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
921#define CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
922
923namespace Catch {
924
925 // ResultWas::OfType enum
926 struct ResultWas { enum OfType {
927 Unknown = -1,
928 Ok = 0,
929 Info = 1,
930 Warning = 2,
931 // TODO: Should explicit skip be considered "not OK" (cf. isOk)? I.e., should it have the failure bit?
932 ExplicitSkip = 4,
933
934 FailureBit = 0x10,
935
936 ExpressionFailed = FailureBit | 1,
937 ExplicitFailure = FailureBit | 2,
938
939 Exception = 0x100 | FailureBit,
940
941 ThrewException = Exception | 1,
942 DidntThrowException = Exception | 2,
943
944 FatalErrorCondition = 0x200 | FailureBit
945
946 }; };
947
948 bool isOk( ResultWas::OfType resultType );
949 bool isJustInfo( int flags );
950
951
952 // ResultDisposition::Flags enum
953 struct ResultDisposition { enum Flags {
954 Normal = 0x01,
955
956 ContinueOnFailure = 0x02, // Failures fail test, but execution continues
957 FalseTest = 0x04, // Prefix expression with !
958 SuppressFail = 0x08 // Failures are reported but do not fail the test
959 }; };
960
961 ResultDisposition::Flags operator | ( ResultDisposition::Flags lhs, ResultDisposition::Flags rhs );
962
963 bool shouldContinueOnFailure( int flags );
964 inline bool isFalseTest( int flags ) { return ( flags & ResultDisposition::FalseTest ) != 0; }
965 bool shouldSuppressFailure( int flags );
966
967} // end namespace Catch
968
969#endif // CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED

1080#ifndef CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
1081#define CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
1082
1083#include <cassert>
1084#include <type_traits>
1085
1086
1087namespace Catch {
1088namespace Detail {
1094 template <typename T>
1095 class unique_ptr {
1096 T* m_ptr;
1097 public:
1098 constexpr unique_ptr(std::nullptr_t = nullptr):
1099 m_ptr{}
1100 {}
1101 explicit constexpr unique_ptr(T* ptr):
1102 m_ptr(ptr)
1103 {}
1104
1105 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
1106 unique_ptr(unique_ptr<U>&& from):
1107 m_ptr(from.release())
1108 {}
1109
1110 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
1111 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr<U>&& from) {
1112 reset(from.release());
1113
1114 return *this;
1115 }
1116
1117 unique_ptr(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
1118 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
1119
1120 unique_ptr(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept:
1121 m_ptr(rhs.m_ptr) {
1122 rhs.m_ptr = nullptr;
1123 }
1124 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept {
1125 reset(rhs.release());
1126
1127 return *this;
1128 }
1129
1130 ~unique_ptr() {
1131 delete m_ptr;
1132 }
1133
1134 T& operator*() {
1135 assert(m_ptr);
1136 return *m_ptr;
1137 }
1138 T const& operator*() const {
1139 assert(m_ptr);
1140 return *m_ptr;
1141 }
1142 T* operator->() noexcept {
1143 assert(m_ptr);
1144 return m_ptr;
1145 }
1146 T const* operator->() const noexcept {
1147 assert(m_ptr);
1148 return m_ptr;
1149 }
1150
1151 T* get() { return m_ptr; }
1152 T const* get() const { return m_ptr; }
1153
1154 void reset(T* ptr = nullptr) {
1155 delete m_ptr;
1156 m_ptr = ptr;
1157 }
1158
1159 T* release() {
1160 auto temp = m_ptr;
1161 m_ptr = nullptr;
1162 return temp;
1163 }
1164
1165 explicit operator bool() const {
1166 return m_ptr;
1167 }
1168
1169 friend void swap(unique_ptr& lhs, unique_ptr& rhs) {
1170 auto temp = lhs.m_ptr;
1171 lhs.m_ptr = rhs.m_ptr;
1172 rhs.m_ptr = temp;
1173 }
1174 };
1175
1177 template <typename T>
1178 class unique_ptr<T[]>;
1179
1180 template <typename T, typename... Args>
1181 unique_ptr<T> make_unique(Args&&... args) {
1182 return unique_ptr<T>(new T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
1183 }
1184
1185
1186} // end namespace Detail
1187} // end namespace Catch
1188
1189#endif // CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED

1342#ifndef CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1343#define CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1344
1345namespace Catch {
1346 namespace Benchmark {
1347 struct OutlierClassification {
1348 int samples_seen = 0;
1349 int low_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR below Q1
1350 int low_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR below Q1
1351 int high_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR above Q3
1352 int high_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR above Q3
1353
1354 int total() const {
1355 return low_severe + low_mild + high_mild + high_severe;
1356 }
1357 };
1358 } // namespace Benchmark
1359} // namespace Catch
1360
1361#endif // CATCH_OUTLIERS_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED

1474 Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> mean;
1475 Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> standardDeviation;
1476 Benchmark::OutlierClassification outliers;
1477 double outlierVariance;
1478
1479 template <typename Duration2>
1480 operator BenchmarkStats<Duration2>() const {
1481 std::vector<Duration2> samples2;
1482 samples2.reserve(samples.size());
1483 for (auto const& sample : samples) {
1484 samples2.push_back(Duration2(sample));
1485 }
1486 return {
1487 info,
1488 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
1489 mean,
1490 standardDeviation,
1491 outliers,
1492 outlierVariance,
1493 };
1494 }
1495 };

1699#define CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED
1700
1701#if defined(_MSC_VER)
1702# include <atomic> // atomic_thread_fence
1703#endif
1704
1705
1706#include <type_traits>
1707
1708namespace Catch {
1709 namespace Benchmark {
1710#if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
1711 template <typename T>
1712 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1713 asm volatile("" : : "g"(p) : "memory");
1714 }
1715 inline void keep_memory() {
1716 asm volatile("" : : : "memory");
1717 }
1718
1719 namespace Detail {
1720 inline void optimizer_barrier() { keep_memory(); }
1721 } // namespace Detail
1722#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
1723
1724#pragma optimize("", off)
1725 template <typename T>
1726 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1727 // thanks @milleniumbug
1728 *reinterpret_cast<char volatile*>(p) = *reinterpret_cast<char const volatile*>(p);
1729 }
1730 // TODO equivalent keep_memory()
1731#pragma optimize("", on)
1732
1733 namespace Detail {
1734 inline void optimizer_barrier() {
1735 std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
1736 }
1737 } // namespace Detail
1738
1739#endif
1740
1741 template <typename T>
1742 inline void deoptimize_value(T&& x) {
1743 keep_memory(&x);
1744 }
1745
1746 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1747 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1748 deoptimize_value(CATCH_FORWARD(fn) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
1749 }
1750
1751 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1752 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1753 CATCH_FORWARD(fn) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1754 }
1755 } // namespace Benchmark
1756} // namespace Catch
1757
1758#endif // CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED

1800 struct is_callable_tester {
1801 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1802 static true_given<decltype(std::declval<Fun>()(std::declval<Args>()...))> test(int);
1803 template <typename...>
1804 static std::false_type test(...);
1805 };

1815 // std::result_of is deprecated in C++17 and removed in C++20. Hence, it is
1816 // replaced with std::invoke_result here.
1817 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1818 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::invoke_result_t<Func, U...>>>;
1819#else
1820 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1821 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::result_of_t<Func(U...)>>>;

1892#include <type_traits>
1893
1894namespace Catch {
1895 namespace Benchmark {
1896 namespace Detail {
1897 template <typename T>
1898 struct CompleteType { using type = T; };
1899 template <>
1900 struct CompleteType<void> { struct type {}; };
1901
1902 template <typename T>
1903 using CompleteType_t = typename CompleteType<T>::type;
1904
1905 template <typename Result>
1906 struct CompleteInvoker {
1907 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1908 static Result invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1909 return CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1910 }
1911 };
1912 template <>
1913 struct CompleteInvoker<void> {
1914 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1915 static CompleteType_t<void> invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1916 CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1917 return {};
1918 }
1919 };
1920
1921 // invoke and not return void :(
1922 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1923 CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>> complete_invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1924 return CompleteInvoker<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>>::invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1925 }
1926
1927 } // namespace Detail
1928
1929 template <typename Fun>
1930 Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun>> user_code(Fun&& fun) {
1931 return Detail::complete_invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun));
1932 }
1933 } // namespace Benchmark
1934} // namespace Catch

1936#endif // CATCH_COMPLETE_INVOKE_HPP_INCLUDED

1938namespace Catch {
1939 namespace Benchmark {
1940 namespace Detail {
1941 struct ChronometerConcept {
1942 virtual void start() = 0;
1943 virtual void finish() = 0;
1944 virtual ~ChronometerConcept(); // = default;
1945
1946 ChronometerConcept() = default;
1947 ChronometerConcept(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1948 ChronometerConcept& operator=(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1949 };
1950 template <typename Clock>
1951 struct ChronometerModel final : public ChronometerConcept {
1952 void start() override { started = Clock::now(); }
1953 void finish() override { finished = Clock::now(); }
1954
1955 ClockDuration<Clock> elapsed() const { return finished - started; }
1956
1957 TimePoint<Clock> started;
1958 TimePoint<Clock> finished;
1959 };
1960 } // namespace Detail
1961
1962 struct Chronometer {
1963 public:
1964 template <typename Fun>
1965 void measure(Fun&& fun) { measure(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), is_callable<Fun(int)>()); }
1966
1967 int runs() const { return repeats; }
1968
1969 Chronometer(Detail::ChronometerConcept& meter, int repeats_)
1970 : impl(&meter)
1971 , repeats(repeats_) {}
1972
1973 private:
1974 template <typename Fun>
1975 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::false_type) {
1976 measure([&fun](int) { return fun(); }, std::true_type());
1977 }
1978
1979 template <typename Fun>
1980 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::true_type) {
1981 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1982 impl->start();
1983 for (int i = 0; i < repeats; ++i) invoke_deoptimized(fun, i);
1984 impl->finish();
1985 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1986 }
1987
1988 Detail::ChronometerConcept* impl;
1989 int repeats;
1990 };
1991 } // namespace Benchmark
1992} // namespace Catch
1993
1994#endif // CATCH_CHRONOMETER_HPP_INCLUDED

2034// Adapted from donated nonius code.
2035
2036#ifndef CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED
2037#define CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED
2038
2039
2040#include <type_traits>
2041
2042namespace Catch {
2043 namespace Benchmark {
2044 namespace Detail {
2045 template <typename T, typename U>
2046 struct is_related
2047 : std::is_same<std::decay_t<T>, std::decay_t<U>> {};
2048
2056 struct BenchmarkFunction {
2057 private:
2058 struct callable {
2059 virtual void call(Chronometer meter) const = 0;
2060 virtual Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> clone() const = 0;
2061 virtual ~callable(); // = default;
2062
2063 callable() = default;
2064 callable(callable const&) = default;
2065 callable& operator=(callable const&) = default;
2066 };
2067 template <typename Fun>
2068 struct model : public callable {
2069 model(Fun&& fun_) : fun(CATCH_MOVE(fun_)) {}
2070 model(Fun const& fun_) : fun(fun_) {}
2071
2072 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> clone() const override {
2073 return Catch::Detail::make_unique<model<Fun>>( *this );
2074 }
2075
2076 void call(Chronometer meter) const override {
2077 call(meter, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
2078 }
2079 void call(Chronometer meter, std::true_type) const {
2080 fun(meter);
2081 }
2082 void call(Chronometer meter, std::false_type) const {
2083 meter.measure(fun);
2084 }
2085
2086 Fun fun;
2087 };
2088
2089 struct do_nothing { void operator()() const {} };
2090
2091 template <typename T>
2092 BenchmarkFunction(model<T>* c) : f(c) {}
2093
2094 public:
2095 BenchmarkFunction()
2096 : f(new model<do_nothing>{ {} }) {}
2097
2098 template <typename Fun,
2099 std::enable_if_t<!is_related<Fun, BenchmarkFunction>::value, int> = 0>
2100 BenchmarkFunction(Fun&& fun)
2101 : f(new model<std::decay_t<Fun>>(CATCH_FORWARD(fun))) {}
2102
2103 BenchmarkFunction( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept:
2104 f( CATCH_MOVE( that.f ) ) {}
2105
2106 BenchmarkFunction(BenchmarkFunction const& that)
2107 : f(that.f->clone()) {}
2108
2109 BenchmarkFunction&
2110 operator=( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept {
2111 f = CATCH_MOVE( that.f );
2112 return *this;
2113 }
2114
2115 BenchmarkFunction& operator=(BenchmarkFunction const& that) {
2116 f = that.f->clone();
2117 return *this;
2118 }
2119
2120 void operator()(Chronometer meter) const { f->call(meter); }
2121
2122 private:
2123 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> f;
2124 };
2125 } // namespace Detail
2126 } // namespace Benchmark
2127} // namespace Catch
2128
2129#endif // CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED

2143 struct repeater {
2144 void operator()(int k) const {
2145 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2146 fun();
2147 }
2148 }
2149 Fun fun;
2150 };

2152 repeater<std::decay_t<Fun>> repeat(Fun&& fun) {

2168
2169// Adapted from donated nonius code.
2170
2171#ifndef CATCH_MEASURE_HPP_INCLUDED
2172#define CATCH_MEASURE_HPP_INCLUDED
2173
2174
2175
2176// Adapted from donated nonius code.
2177
2178#ifndef CATCH_TIMING_HPP_INCLUDED
2179#define CATCH_TIMING_HPP_INCLUDED
2180
2181
2182#include <type_traits>
2183
2184namespace Catch {
2185 namespace Benchmark {
2186 template <typename Duration, typename Result>
2187 struct Timing {
2188 Duration elapsed;
2189 Result result;
2190 int iterations;
2191 };
2192 template <typename Clock, typename Func, typename... Args>
2193 using TimingOf = Timing<ClockDuration<Clock>, Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Func, Args...>>>;
2194 } // namespace Benchmark
2195} // namespace Catch
2196
2197#endif // CATCH_TIMING_HPP_INCLUDED
2198
2199namespace Catch {
2200 namespace Benchmark {
2201 namespace Detail {
2202 template <typename Clock, typename Fun, typename... Args>
2203 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Args...> measure(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
2204 auto start = Clock::now();
2205 auto&& r = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
2206 auto end = Clock::now();
2207 auto delta = end - start;
2208 return { delta, CATCH_FORWARD(r), 1 };
2209 }
2210 } // namespace Detail
2211 } // namespace Benchmark
2212} // namespace Catch
2213
2214#endif // CATCH_MEASURE_HPP_INCLUDED
2215
2216#include <type_traits>
2217
2218namespace Catch {
2219 namespace Benchmark {
2220 namespace Detail {
2221 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2222 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, int> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::false_type) {
2223 return Detail::measure<Clock>(fun, iters);
2224 }
2225 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2226 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Chronometer> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::true_type) {
2227 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> meter;
2228 auto&& result = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, Chronometer(meter, iters));
2229
2230 return { meter.elapsed(), CATCH_MOVE(result), iters };
2231 }
2232
2233 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2234 using run_for_at_least_argument_t = std::conditional_t<is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>::value, Chronometer, int>;
2235
2236
2237 [[noreturn]]
2238 void throw_optimized_away_error();
2239
2240 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2241 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, run_for_at_least_argument_t<Clock, Fun>>
2242 run_for_at_least(ClockDuration<Clock> how_long,
2243 const int initial_iterations,
2244 Fun&& fun) {
2245 auto iters = initial_iterations;
2246 while (iters < (1 << 30)) {
2247 auto&& Timing = measure_one<Clock>(fun, iters, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
2248
2249 if (Timing.elapsed >= how_long) {
2250 return { Timing.elapsed, CATCH_MOVE(Timing.result), iters };
2251 }
2252 iters *= 2;
2253 }
2254 throw_optimized_away_error();
2255 }
2256 } // namespace Detail
2257 } // namespace Benchmark
2258} // namespace Catch
2259
2260#endif // CATCH_RUN_FOR_AT_LEAST_HPP_INCLUDED
2261
2262#include <algorithm>
2263#include <iterator>
2264
2265namespace Catch {
2266 namespace Benchmark {
2267 template <typename Duration>
2268 struct ExecutionPlan {
2269 int iterations_per_sample;
2270 Duration estimated_duration;
2271 Detail::BenchmarkFunction benchmark;
2272 Duration warmup_time;
2273 int warmup_iterations;
2274
2275 template <typename Duration2>
2276 operator ExecutionPlan<Duration2>() const {
2277 return { iterations_per_sample, estimated_duration, benchmark, warmup_time, warmup_iterations };
2278 }
2279
2280 template <typename Clock>
2281 std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> run(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
2282 // warmup a bit
2283 Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_iterations, Detail::repeat(now<Clock>{}));
2284
2285 std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> times;
2286 times.reserve(cfg.benchmarkSamples());
2287 std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), cfg.benchmarkSamples(), [this, env] {
2288 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> model;
2289 this->benchmark(Chronometer(model, iterations_per_sample));
2290 auto sample_time = model.elapsed() - env.clock_cost.mean;
2291 if (sample_time < FloatDuration<Clock>::zero()) sample_time = FloatDuration<Clock>::zero();
2292 return sample_time / iterations_per_sample;
2293 });
2294 return times;
2295 }
2296 };
2297 } // namespace Benchmark
2298} // namespace Catch
2299
2300#endif // CATCH_EXECUTION_PLAN_HPP_INCLUDED

2316#include <algorithm>

2321
2322namespace Catch {
2323 namespace Benchmark {
2324 namespace Detail {
2325 using sample = std::vector<double>;
2326
2327 // Used when we know we want == comparison of two doubles
2328 // to centralize warning suppression
2329 bool directCompare( double lhs, double rhs );
2330
2331 double weighted_average_quantile(int k, int q, std::vector<double>::iterator first, std::vector<double>::iterator last);
2332
2333 template <typename Iterator>
2334 OutlierClassification classify_outliers(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2335 std::vector<double> copy(first, last);
2336
2337 auto q1 = weighted_average_quantile(1, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
2338 auto q3 = weighted_average_quantile(3, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
2339 auto iqr = q3 - q1;
2340 auto los = q1 - (iqr * 3.);
2341 auto lom = q1 - (iqr * 1.5);
2342 auto him = q3 + (iqr * 1.5);
2343 auto his = q3 + (iqr * 3.);
2344
2345 OutlierClassification o;
2346 for (; first != last; ++first) {
2347 auto&& t = *first;
2348 if (t < los) ++o.low_severe;
2349 else if (t < lom) ++o.low_mild;
2350 else if (t > his) ++o.high_severe;
2351 else if (t > him) ++o.high_mild;
2352 ++o.samples_seen;
2353 }
2354 return o;
2355 }
2356
2357 template <typename Iterator>
2358 double mean(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2359 auto count = last - first;
2360 double sum = std::accumulate(first, last, 0.);
2361 return sum / static_cast<double>(count);
2362 }
2363
2364 template <typename Estimator, typename Iterator>
2365 sample jackknife(Estimator&& estimator, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2366 auto n = static_cast<size_t>(last - first);
2367 auto second = first;
2368 ++second;
2369 sample results;
2370 results.reserve(n);
2371
2372 for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it) {
2373 std::iter_swap(it, first);
2374 results.push_back(estimator(second, last));
2375 }
2376
2377 return results;
2378 }
2379
2380 inline double normal_cdf(double x) {
2381 return std::erfc(-x / std::sqrt(2.0)) / 2.0;
2382 }
2383
2384 double erfc_inv(double x);
2385
2386 double normal_quantile(double p);
2387
2388 template <typename Iterator, typename Estimator>
2389 Estimate<double> bootstrap(double confidence_level, Iterator first, Iterator last, sample const& resample, Estimator&& estimator) {
2390 auto n_samples = last - first;
2391
2392 double point = estimator(first, last);
2393 // Degenerate case with a single sample
2394 if (n_samples == 1) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
2395
2396 sample jack = jackknife(estimator, first, last);
2397 double jack_mean = mean(jack.begin(), jack.end());
2398 double sum_squares, sum_cubes;
2399 std::tie(sum_squares, sum_cubes) = std::accumulate(jack.begin(), jack.end(), std::make_pair(0., 0.), [jack_mean](std::pair<double, double> sqcb, double x) -> std::pair<double, double> {
2400 auto d = jack_mean - x;
2401 auto d2 = d * d;
2402 auto d3 = d2 * d;
2403 return { sqcb.first + d2, sqcb.second + d3 };
2404 });
2405
2406 double accel = sum_cubes / (6 * std::pow(sum_squares, 1.5));
2407 long n = static_cast<long>(resample.size());
2408 double prob_n = std::count_if(resample.begin(), resample.end(), [point](double x) { return x < point; }) / static_cast<double>(n);
2409 // degenerate case with uniform samples
2410 if ( directCompare( prob_n, 0. ) ) {
2411 return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
2412 }
2413
2414 double bias = normal_quantile(prob_n);
2415 double z1 = normal_quantile((1. - confidence_level) / 2.);
2416
2417 auto cumn = [n]( double x ) -> long {
2418 return std::lround( normal_cdf( x ) * static_cast<double>(n) );
2419 };
2420 auto a = [bias, accel](double b) { return bias + b / (1. - accel * b); };
2421 double b1 = bias + z1;
2422 double b2 = bias - z1;
2423 double a1 = a(b1);
2424 double a2 = a(b2);
2425 auto lo = static_cast<size_t>((std::max)(cumn(a1), 0l));
2426 auto hi = static_cast<size_t>((std::min)(cumn(a2), n - 1));
2427
2428 return { point, resample[lo], resample[hi], confidence_level };
2429 }
2430
2431 double outlier_variance(Estimate<double> mean, Estimate<double> stddev, int n);
2432
2433 struct bootstrap_analysis {
2434 Estimate<double> mean;
2435 Estimate<double> standard_deviation;
2436 double outlier_variance;
2437 };
2438
2439 bootstrap_analysis analyse_samples(double confidence_level, unsigned int n_resamples, std::vector<double>::iterator first, std::vector<double>::iterator last);
2440 } // namespace Detail
2441 } // namespace Benchmark
2442} // namespace Catch
2443
2444#endif // CATCH_STATS_HPP_INCLUDED

2451namespace Catch {
2452 namespace Benchmark {

2454 template <typename Clock>
2455 std::vector<double> resolution(int k) {
2456 std::vector<TimePoint<Clock>> times;
2457 times.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(k + 1));
2458 std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), k + 1, now<Clock>{});
2459
2460 std::vector<double> deltas;
2461 deltas.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(k));
2462 std::transform(std::next(times.begin()), times.end(), times.begin(),
2463 std::back_inserter(deltas),
2464 [](TimePoint<Clock> a, TimePoint<Clock> b) { return static_cast<double>((a - b).count()); });
2465
2466 return deltas;
2467 }
2468
2469 const auto warmup_iterations = 10000;
2470 const auto warmup_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(100);
2471 const auto minimum_ticks = 1000;
2472 const auto warmup_seed = 10000;
2473 const auto clock_resolution_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(500);
2474 const auto clock_cost_estimation_time_limit = std::chrono::seconds(1);
2475 const auto clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit = 100000;
2476 const auto clock_cost_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(10);
2477 const auto clock_cost_estimation_iterations = 10000;
2478
2479 template <typename Clock>
2480 int warmup() {
2481 return run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_seed, &resolution<Clock>)
2482 .iterations;
2483 }
2484 template <typename Clock>
2485 EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_resolution(int iterations) {
2486 auto r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_resolution_estimation_time), iterations, &resolution<Clock>)
2487 .result;
2488 return {
2489 FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(r.begin(), r.end())),
2490 classify_outliers(r.begin(), r.end()),
2491 };
2492 }
2493 template <typename Clock>
2494 EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_cost(FloatDuration<Clock> resolution) {
2495 auto time_limit = (std::min)(
2496 resolution * clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit,
2497 FloatDuration<Clock>(clock_cost_estimation_time_limit));
2498 auto time_clock = [](int k) {
2499 return Detail::measure<Clock>([k] {
2500 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2501 volatile auto ignored = Clock::now();
2502 (void)ignored;
2503 }
2504 }).elapsed;
2505 };
2506 time_clock(1);
2507 int iters = clock_cost_estimation_iterations;
2508 auto&& r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_cost_estimation_time), iters, time_clock);
2509 std::vector<double> times;
2510 int nsamples = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(time_limit / r.elapsed));
2511 times.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(nsamples));
2512 std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), nsamples, [time_clock, &r] {
2513 return static_cast<double>((time_clock(r.iterations) / r.iterations).count());
2514 });
2515 return {
2516 FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(times.begin(), times.end())),
2517 classify_outliers(times.begin(), times.end()),
2518 };
2519 }
2520
2521 template <typename Clock>
2522 Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> measure_environment() {
2523#if defined(__clang__)
2524# pragma clang diagnostic push
2525# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wexit-time-destructors"
2526#endif
2527 static Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>> env;
2528#if defined(__clang__)
2529# pragma clang diagnostic pop
2530#endif
2531 if (env) {
2532 return *env;
2533 }
2534
2535 auto iters = Detail::warmup<Clock>();
2536 auto resolution = Detail::estimate_clock_resolution<Clock>(iters);
2537 auto cost = Detail::estimate_clock_cost<Clock>(resolution.mean);
2538
2539 env = Catch::Detail::make_unique<Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>>( Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>{resolution, cost} );
2540 return *env;
2541 }
2542 } // namespace Detail
2543 } // namespace Benchmark
2544} // namespace Catch

2546#endif // CATCH_ESTIMATE_CLOCK_HPP_INCLUDED

2568 template <typename Duration>
2569 struct SampleAnalysis {

2581 return {
2582 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
2583 mean,
2584 standard_deviation,

2586 outlier_variance,

2602 template <typename Duration, typename Iterator>
2603 SampleAnalysis<Duration> analyse(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<Duration>, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2604 if (!cfg.benchmarkNoAnalysis()) {
2605 std::vector<double> samples;
2606 samples.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
2607 std::transform(first, last, std::back_inserter(samples), [](Duration d) { return d.count(); });
2608
2609 auto analysis = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::analyse_samples(cfg.benchmarkConfidenceInterval(), cfg.benchmarkResamples(), samples.begin(), samples.end());
2610 auto outliers = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::classify_outliers(samples.begin(), samples.end());
2611
2612 auto wrap_estimate = [](Estimate<double> e) {
2613 return Estimate<Duration> {
2614 Duration(e.point),
2615 Duration(e.lower_bound),
2616 Duration(e.upper_bound),
2617 e.confidence_interval,
2618 };
2619 };
2620 std::vector<Duration> samples2;
2621 samples2.reserve(samples.size());
2622 std::transform(samples.begin(), samples.end(), std::back_inserter(samples2), [](double d) { return Duration(d); });
2623 return {
2624 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
2625 wrap_estimate(analysis.mean),
2626 wrap_estimate(analysis.standard_deviation),
2627 outliers,
2628 analysis.outlier_variance,
2629 };
2630 } else {
2631 std::vector<Duration> samples;
2632 samples.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
2633
2634 Duration mean = Duration(0);
2635 int i = 0;
2636 for (auto it = first; it < last; ++it, ++i) {
2637 samples.push_back(Duration(*it));
2638 mean += Duration(*it);
2639 }
2640 mean /= i;
2641
2642 return {
2643 CATCH_MOVE(samples),
2644 Estimate<Duration>{mean, mean, mean, 0.0},
2645 Estimate<Duration>{Duration(0), Duration(0), Duration(0), 0.0},
2646 OutlierClassification{},
2647 0.0
2648 };
2649 }
2650 }
2651 } // namespace Detail
2652 } // namespace Benchmark
2653} // namespace Catch
2654
2655#endif // CATCH_ANALYSE_HPP_INCLUDED

2657#include <algorithm>
2658#include <functional>
2659#include <string>
2660#include <vector>
2661#include <cmath>
2662
2663namespace Catch {
2664 namespace Benchmark {
2665 struct Benchmark {
2666 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName)
2667 : name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2668
2669 template <class FUN>
2670 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName , FUN &&func)
2671 : fun(CATCH_MOVE(func)), name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2672
2673 template <typename Clock>
2674 ExecutionPlan<FloatDuration<Clock>> prepare(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
2675 auto min_time = env.clock_resolution.mean * Detail::minimum_ticks;
2676 auto run_time = std::max(min_time, std::chrono::duration_cast<decltype(min_time)>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()));
2677 auto&& test = Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(run_time), 1, fun);
2678 int new_iters = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(min_time * test.iterations / test.elapsed));
2679 return { new_iters, test.elapsed / test.iterations * new_iters * cfg.benchmarkSamples(), fun, std::chrono::duration_cast<FloatDuration<Clock>>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()), Detail::warmup_iterations };
2680 }
2681
2682 template <typename Clock = default_clock>
2683 void run() {
2684 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2685
2686 auto env = Detail::measure_environment<Clock>();
2687
2688 getResultCapture().benchmarkPreparing(name);
2689 CATCH_TRY{
2690 auto plan = user_code([&] {
2691 return prepare<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2692 });
2693
2694 BenchmarkInfo info {
2695 CATCH_MOVE(name),
2696 plan.estimated_duration.count(),
2697 plan.iterations_per_sample,
2698 cfg->benchmarkSamples(),
2699 cfg->benchmarkResamples(),
2700 env.clock_resolution.mean.count(),
2701 env.clock_cost.mean.count()
2702 };
2703
2704 getResultCapture().benchmarkStarting(info);
2705
2706 auto samples = user_code([&] {
2707 return plan.template run<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2708 });
2709
2710 auto analysis = Detail::analyse(*cfg, env, samples.begin(), samples.end());
2711 BenchmarkStats<FloatDuration<Clock>> stats{ CATCH_MOVE(info), CATCH_MOVE(analysis.samples), analysis.mean, analysis.standard_deviation, analysis.outliers, analysis.outlier_variance };
2712 getResultCapture().benchmarkEnded(stats);
2713 } CATCH_CATCH_ANON (TestFailureException) {
2714 getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed("Benchmark failed due to failed assertion"_sr);
2715 } CATCH_CATCH_ALL{
2716 getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed(translateActiveException());
2717 // We let the exception go further up so that the
2718 // test case is marked as failed.
2719 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
2720 }
2721 }
2722
2723 // sets lambda to be used in fun *and* executes benchmark!
2724 template <typename Fun, std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_related<Fun, Benchmark>::value, int> = 0>
2725 Benchmark & operator=(Fun func) {
2726 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2727 if (!cfg->skipBenchmarks()) {
2728 fun = Detail::BenchmarkFunction(func);
2729 run();
2730 }
2731 return *this;
2732 }
2733
2734 explicit operator bool() {
2735 return true;
2736 }
2737
2738 private:
2739 Detail::BenchmarkFunction fun;
2740 std::string name;
2741 };
2742 }
2743} // namespace Catch

2781#include <type_traits>

2783namespace Catch {
2784 namespace Benchmark {
2785 namespace Detail {
2786 template <typename T, bool Destruct>
2787 struct ObjectStorage
2788 {
2789 ObjectStorage() = default;
2790
2791 ObjectStorage(const ObjectStorage& other)
2792 {
2793 new(&data) T(other.stored_object());
2794 }
2795
2796 ObjectStorage(ObjectStorage&& other)
2797 {
2798 new(data) T(CATCH_MOVE(other.stored_object()));
2799 }
2800
2801 ~ObjectStorage() { destruct_on_exit<T>(); }
2802
2803 template <typename... Args>
2804 void construct(Args&&... args)
2805 {
2806 new (data) T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
2807 }
2808
2809 template <bool AllowManualDestruction = !Destruct>
2810 std::enable_if_t<AllowManualDestruction> destruct()
2811 {
2812 stored_object().~T();
2813 }
2814
2815 private:
2816 // If this is a constructor benchmark, destruct the underlying object
2817 template <typename U>
2818 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { destruct<true>(); }
2819 // Otherwise, don't
2820 template <typename U>
2821 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<!Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { }
2822
2823#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2824# pragma GCC diagnostic push
2825# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wstrict-aliasing"
2826#endif
2827 T& stored_object() { return *reinterpret_cast<T*>( data ); }
2828
2829 T const& stored_object() const {
2830 return *reinterpret_cast<T const*>( data );
2831 }
2832#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2833# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2834#endif
2835
2836 alignas( T ) unsigned char data[sizeof( T )]{};
2837 };
2838 } // namespace Detail
2839
2840 template <typename T>
2841 using storage_for = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, true>;
2842
2843 template <typename T>
2844 using destructable_object = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, false>;
2845 } // namespace Benchmark
2846} // namespace Catch

2905
2906namespace Catch {
2907
2908 class ReusableStringStream : Detail::NonCopyable {
2909 std::size_t m_index;
2910 std::ostream* m_oss;
2911 public:
2912 ReusableStringStream();
2913 ~ReusableStringStream();
2914
2916 std::string str() const;
2918 void str(std::string const& str);
2919
2920#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2921#pragma GCC diagnostic push
2922// Old versions of GCC do not understand -Wnonnull-compare
2923#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wpragmas"
2924// Streaming a function pointer triggers Waddress and Wnonnull-compare
2925// on GCC, because it implicitly converts it to bool and then decides
2926// that the check it uses (a? true : false) is tautological and cannot
2927// be null...
2928#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Waddress"
2929#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wnonnull-compare"
2930#endif
2931
2932 template<typename T>
2933 auto operator << ( T const& value ) -> ReusableStringStream& {
2934 *m_oss << value;
2935 return *this;
2936 }
2937
2938#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2939#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2940#endif
2941 auto get() -> std::ostream& { return *m_oss; }
2942 };
2943}
2944
2945#endif // CATCH_REUSABLE_STRING_STREAM_HPP_INCLUDED

2987 class IMutableEnumValuesRegistry {
2988 public:
2989 virtual ~IMutableEnumValuesRegistry(); // = default;
2990
2991 virtual Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::vector<int> const& values ) = 0;
2992
2993 template<typename E>
2994 Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::initializer_list<E> values ) {
2995 static_assert(sizeof(int) >= sizeof(E), "Cannot serialize enum to int");
2996 std::vector<int> intValues;
2997 intValues.reserve( values.size() );
2998 for( auto enumValue : values )
2999 intValues.push_back( static_cast<int>( enumValue ) );
3000 return registerEnum( enumName, allEnums, intValues );
3001 }
3002 };

3028 inline std::size_t catch_strnlen(const char *str, std::size_t n) {
3029 auto ret = std::char_traits<char>::find(str, n, '\0');
3030 if (ret != nullptr) {
3031 return static_cast<std::size_t>(ret - str);
3032 }
3033 return n;
3034 }

3036 constexpr StringRef unprintableString = "{?}"_sr;
3037
3039 std::string convertIntoString( StringRef string, bool escapeInvisibles );
3040
3043 std::string convertIntoString( StringRef string );
3044
3045 std::string rawMemoryToString( const void *object, std::size_t size );
3046
3047 template<typename T>
3048 std::string rawMemoryToString( const T& object ) {
3049 return rawMemoryToString( &object, sizeof(object) );
3050 }
3051
3052 template<typename T>
3053 class IsStreamInsertable {
3054 template<typename Stream, typename U>
3055 static auto test(int)
3056 -> decltype(std::declval<Stream&>() << std::declval<U>(), std::true_type());
3057
3058 template<typename, typename>
3059 static auto test(...)->std::false_type;
3060
3061 public:
3062 static const bool value = decltype(test<std::ostream, const T&>(0))::value;
3063 };
3064
3065 template<typename E>
3066 std::string convertUnknownEnumToString( E e );
3067
3068 template<typename T>
3069 std::enable_if_t<
3070 !std::is_enum<T>::value && !std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
3071 std::string> convertUnstreamable( T const& ) {
3072 return std::string(Detail::unprintableString);
3073 }
3074 template<typename T>
3075 std::enable_if_t<
3076 !std::is_enum<T>::value && std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
3077 std::string> convertUnstreamable(T const& ex) {
3078 return ex.what();
3079 }
3080
3081
3082 template<typename T>
3083 std::enable_if_t<
3084 std::is_enum<T>::value,
3085 std::string> convertUnstreamable( T const& value ) {
3086 return convertUnknownEnumToString( value );
3087 }
3088
3089#if defined(_MANAGED)
3091 template<typename T>
3092 std::string clrReferenceToString( T^ ref ) {
3093 if (ref == nullptr)
3094 return std::string("null");
3095 auto bytes = System::Text::Encoding::UTF8->GetBytes(ref->ToString());
3096 cli::pin_ptr<System::Byte> p = &bytes[0];
3097 return std::string(reinterpret_cast<char const *>(p), bytes->Length);
3098 }
3099#endif

3105 template <typename T, typename = void>
3106 struct StringMaker {
3107 template <typename Fake = T>
3108 static
3109 std::enable_if_t<::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
3110 convert(const Fake& value) {
3111 ReusableStringStream rss;
3112 // NB: call using the function-like syntax to avoid ambiguity with
3113 // user-defined templated operator<< under clang.
3114 rss.operator<<(value);
3115 return rss.str();
3116 }
3117
3118 template <typename Fake = T>
3119 static
3120 std::enable_if_t<!::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
3121 convert( const Fake& value ) {
3122#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER)
3123 return Detail::convertUnstreamable(value);
3124#else
3125 return CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER(value);
3126#endif
3127 }
3128 };

3327 namespace Detail {
3328 template<typename InputIterator, typename Sentinel = InputIterator>
3329 std::string rangeToString(InputIterator first, Sentinel last) {
3330 ReusableStringStream rss;
3331 rss << "{ ";
3332 if (first != last) {
3333 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
3334 for (++first; first != last; ++first)
3335 rss << ", " << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
3336 }
3337 rss << " }";
3338 return rss.str();
3339 }
3340 }

3488 // Handle vector<bool> specially
3489 template<typename Allocator>
3490 std::string rangeToString( std::vector<bool, Allocator> const& v ) {
3491 ReusableStringStream rss;
3492 rss << "{ ";
3493 bool first = true;
3494 for( bool b : v ) {
3495 if( first )
3496 first = false;
3497 else
3498 rss << ", ";
3499 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify( b );
3500 }
3501 rss << " }";
3502 return rss.str();
3503 }

3601 // std::chrono::time_point specialization
3602 // Generic time_point cannot be specialized, only std::chrono::time_point<system_clock>
3603 template<typename Clock, typename Duration>
3604 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration>> {
3605 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3606 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(time_point.time_since_epoch()) + " since epoch";
3607 }
3608 };
3609 // std::chrono::time_point<system_clock> specialization
3610 template<typename Duration>
3611 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration>> {
3612 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3613 auto converted = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(time_point);
3614
3615#ifdef _MSC_VER
3616 std::tm timeInfo = {};
3617 gmtime_s(&timeInfo, &converted);
3618#else
3619 std::tm* timeInfo = std::gmtime(&converted);
3620#endif
3621
3622 auto const timeStampSize = sizeof("2017-01-16T17:06:45Z");
3623 char timeStamp[timeStampSize];
3624 const char * const fmt = "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ";
3625
3626#ifdef _MSC_VER
3627 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, &timeInfo);
3628#else
3629 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, timeInfo);
3630#endif
3631 return std::string(timeStamp, timeStampSize - 1);
3632 }
3633 };
3634}

3637#define INTERNAL_CATCH_REGISTER_ENUM( enumName, ... ) \
3638namespace Catch { \
3639 template<> struct StringMaker<enumName> { \
3640 static std::string convert( enumName value ) { \
3641 static const auto& enumInfo = ::Catch::getMutableRegistryHub().getMutableEnumValuesRegistry().registerEnum( #enumName, #__VA_ARGS__, { __VA_ARGS__ } ); \
3642 return static_cast<std::string>(enumInfo.lookup( static_cast<int>( value ) )); \
3643 } \
3644 }; \
3645}

3658
3659 class Approx {
3660 private:
3661 bool equalityComparisonImpl(double other) const;
3662 // Sets and validates the new margin (margin >= 0)
3663 void setMargin(double margin);
3664 // Sets and validates the new epsilon (0 < epsilon < 1)
3665 void setEpsilon(double epsilon);
3666
3667 public:
3668 explicit Approx ( double value );
3669
3670 static Approx custom();
3671
3672 Approx operator-() const;
3673
3674 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3675 Approx operator()( T const& value ) const {
3676 Approx approx( static_cast<double>(value) );
3677 approx.m_epsilon = m_epsilon;
3678 approx.m_margin = m_margin;
3679 approx.m_scale = m_scale;
3680 return approx;
3681 }
3682
3683 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3684 explicit Approx( T const& value ): Approx(static_cast<double>(value))
3685 {}
3686
3687
3688 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3689 friend bool operator == ( const T& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3690 auto lhs_v = static_cast<double>(lhs);
3691 return rhs.equalityComparisonImpl(lhs_v);
3692 }
3693
3694 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3695 friend bool operator == ( Approx const& lhs, const T& rhs ) {
3696 return operator==( rhs, lhs );
3697 }
3698
3699 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3700 friend bool operator != ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3701 return !operator==( lhs, rhs );
3702 }
3703
3704 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3705 friend bool operator != ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3706 return !operator==( rhs, lhs );
3707 }
3708
3709 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3710 friend bool operator <= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3711 return static_cast<double>(lhs) < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3712 }
3713
3714 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3715 friend bool operator <= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3716 return lhs.m_value < static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3717 }
3718
3719 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3720 friend bool operator >= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3721 return static_cast<double>(lhs) > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3722 }
3723
3724 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3725 friend bool operator >= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3726 return lhs.m_value > static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3727 }
3728
3729 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3730 Approx& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
3731 const auto epsilonAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newEpsilon);
3732 setEpsilon(epsilonAsDouble);
3733 return *this;
3734 }
3735
3736 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3737 Approx& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
3738 const auto marginAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newMargin);
3739 setMargin(marginAsDouble);
3740 return *this;
3741 }
3742
3743 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3744 Approx& scale( T const& newScale ) {
3745 m_scale = static_cast<double>(newScale);
3746 return *this;
3747 }
3748
3749 std::string toString() const;
3750
3751 private:
3752 double m_epsilon;
3753 double m_margin;
3754 double m_scale;
3755 double m_value;
3756 };
3757
3758namespace literals {
3759 Approx operator ""_a(long double val);
3760 Approx operator ""_a(unsigned long long val);
3761} // end namespace literals
3762
3763template<>
3764struct StringMaker<Catch::Approx> {
3765 static std::string convert(Catch::Approx const& value);
3766};
3767
3768} // end namespace Catch

3935#define CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED
3936
3937#include <cassert>
3938
3939namespace Catch {
3940
3941 // An optional type
3942 template<typename T>
3943 class Optional {
3944 public:
3945 Optional() : nullableValue( nullptr ) {}
3946 Optional( T const& _value )
3947 : nullableValue( new( storage ) T( _value ) )
3948 {}
3949 Optional( Optional const& _other )
3950 : nullableValue( _other ? new( storage ) T( *_other ) : nullptr )
3951 {}
3952
3953 ~Optional() {
3954 reset();
3955 }
3956
3957 Optional& operator= ( Optional const& _other ) {
3958 if( &_other != this ) {
3959 reset();
3960 if( _other )
3961 nullableValue = new( storage ) T( *_other );
3962 }
3963 return *this;
3964 }
3965 Optional& operator = ( T const& _value ) {
3966 reset();
3967 nullableValue = new( storage ) T( _value );
3968 return *this;
3969 }
3970
3971 void reset() {
3972 if( nullableValue )
3973 nullableValue->~T();
3974 nullableValue = nullptr;
3975 }
3976
3977 T& operator*() {
3978 assert(nullableValue);
3979 return *nullableValue;
3980 }
3981 T const& operator*() const {
3982 assert(nullableValue);
3983 return *nullableValue;
3984 }
3985 T* operator->() {
3986 assert(nullableValue);
3987 return nullableValue;
3988 }
3989 const T* operator->() const {
3990 assert(nullableValue);
3991 return nullableValue;
3992 }
3993
3994 T valueOr( T const& defaultValue ) const {
3995 return nullableValue ? *nullableValue : defaultValue;
3996 }
3997
3998 bool some() const { return nullableValue != nullptr; }
3999 bool none() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
4000
4001 bool operator !() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
4002 explicit operator bool() const {
4003 return some();
4004 }
4005
4006 friend bool operator==(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
4007 if (a.none() && b.none()) {
4008 return true;
4009 } else if (a.some() && b.some()) {
4010 return *a == *b;
4011 } else {
4012 return false;
4013 }
4014 }
4015 friend bool operator!=(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
4016 return !( a == b );
4017 }
4018
4019 private:
4020 T *nullableValue;
4021 alignas(alignof(T)) char storage[sizeof(T)];
4022 };
4023
4024} // end namespace Catch
4025
4026#endif // CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED

4450 m_stream << value;
4451 return *this;

4458 MessageBuilder( StringRef macroName,
4459 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo,
4460 ResultWas::OfType type ):

4483 class Capturer {

4485 IResultCapture& m_resultCapture = getResultCapture();
4486 size_t m_captured = 0;
4487 public:
4488 Capturer( StringRef macroName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, ResultWas::OfType resultType, StringRef names );
4489

4491 Capturer& operator=(Capturer const&) = delete;

4493 ~Capturer();
4494
4495 void captureValue( size_t index, std::string const& value );
4496
4497 template<typename T>
4498 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value ) {
4499 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify( value ) );
4500 }
4501
4502 template<typename T, typename... Ts>
4503 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value, Ts const&... values ) {
4504 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify(value) );
4505 captureValues( index+1, values... );
4506 }
4507 };
4508
4509} // end namespace Catch
4510
4512#define INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( macroName, messageType, resultDisposition, ... ) \
4513 do { \
4514 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), resultDisposition ); \
4515 catchAssertionHandler.handleMessage( messageType, ( Catch::MessageStream() << __VA_ARGS__ + ::Catch::StreamEndStop() ).m_stream.str() ); \
4516 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
4517 } while( false )
4518
4520#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( varName, macroName, ... ) \
4521 Catch::Capturer varName( macroName, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info, #__VA_ARGS__ ); \
4522 varName.captureValues( 0, __VA_ARGS__ )
4523
4525#define INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4526 const Catch::ScopedMessage INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( scopedMessage )( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4527
4529#define INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4530 Catch::getResultCapture().emplaceUnscopedMessage( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4531
4532
4533#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4534
4535 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "CATCH_INFO", msg )
4536 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4537 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4538 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CATCH_CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )
4539
4540#elif defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4541
4542 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4543 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4544 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) (void)(0)
4545 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) (void)(0)
4546
4547#elif !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4548
4549 #define INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "INFO", msg )
4550 #define UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4551 #define WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4552 #define CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )
4553
4554#elif !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4555
4556 #define INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4557 #define UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4558 #define WARN( msg ) (void)(0)

4630 struct fake_arg {
4631 template <typename T>
4632 operator T();
4633 };
4634
4635 template <typename F, typename = void>
4636 struct is_unary_function : std::false_type {};
4637
4638 template <typename F>
4639 struct is_unary_function<
4640 F,
4641 Catch::Detail::void_t<decltype(
4642 std::declval<F>()( fake_arg() ) )
4643 >
4644 > : std::true_type {};
4645
4646 // Traits for extracting arg and return type of lambdas (for single
4647 // argument lambdas)
4648 template <typename L>
4649 struct UnaryLambdaTraits
4650 : UnaryLambdaTraits<decltype( &L::operator() )> {};
4651
4652 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename... Args>
4653 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( Args... ) const> {
4654 static const bool isValid = false;
4655 };
4656
4657 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename ArgT>
4658 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( ArgT ) const> {
4659 static const bool isValid = true;
4660 using ArgType = std::remove_const_t<std::remove_reference_t<ArgT>>;
4661 using ReturnType = ReturnT;
4662 };
4663
4664 class TokenStream;
4665
4666 // Wraps a token coming from a token stream. These may not directly
4667 // correspond to strings as a single string may encode an option +
4668 // its argument if the : or = form is used
4669 enum class TokenType { Option, Argument };
4670 struct Token {
4671 TokenType type;
4672 std::string token;
4673 };
4674
4675 // Abstracts iterators into args as a stream of tokens, with option
4676 // arguments uniformly handled
4677 class TokenStream {
4678 using Iterator = std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator;
4679 Iterator it;
4680 Iterator itEnd;
4681 std::vector<Token> m_tokenBuffer;
4682
4683 void loadBuffer();
4684
4685 public:
4686 explicit TokenStream( Args const& args );
4687 TokenStream( Iterator it, Iterator itEnd );
4688
4689 explicit operator bool() const {
4690 return !m_tokenBuffer.empty() || it != itEnd;
4691 }
4692
4693 size_t count() const {
4694 return m_tokenBuffer.size() + ( itEnd - it );
4695 }
4696
4697 Token operator*() const {
4698 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4699 return m_tokenBuffer.front();
4700 }
4701
4702 Token const* operator->() const {
4703 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4704 return &m_tokenBuffer.front();
4705 }
4706
4707 TokenStream& operator++();
4708 };
4709
4711 enum class ResultType {
4712 Ok,
4713 LogicError,
4715 RuntimeError
4716 };
4717
4718 class ResultBase {
4719 protected:
4720 ResultBase( ResultType type ): m_type( type ) {}
4721 virtual ~ResultBase(); // = default;
4722
4723
4724 ResultBase(ResultBase const&) = default;
4725 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase const&) = default;
4726 ResultBase(ResultBase&&) = default;
4727 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase&&) = default;
4728
4729 virtual void enforceOk() const = 0;
4730
4731 ResultType m_type;
4732 };
4733
4734 template <typename T> class ResultValueBase : public ResultBase {
4735 public:
4736 auto value() const -> T const& {
4737 enforceOk();
4738 return m_value;
4739 }
4740
4741 protected:
4742 ResultValueBase( ResultType type ): ResultBase( type ) {}
4743
4744 ResultValueBase( ResultValueBase const& other ):
4745 ResultBase( other ) {
4746 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4747 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4748 }
4749
4750 ResultValueBase( ResultType, T const& value ): ResultBase( ResultType::Ok ) {
4751 new ( &m_value ) T( value );
4752 }
4753
4754 auto operator=( ResultValueBase const& other )
4755 -> ResultValueBase& {
4756 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4757 m_value.~T();
4758 ResultBase::operator=( other );
4759 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4760 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4761 return *this;
4762 }
4763
4764 ~ResultValueBase() override {
4765 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4766 m_value.~T();
4767 }
4768
4769 union {
4770 T m_value;
4771 };
4772 };
4773
4774 template <> class ResultValueBase<void> : public ResultBase {
4775 protected:
4776 using ResultBase::ResultBase;
4777 };
4778
4779 template <typename T = void>
4780 class BasicResult : public ResultValueBase<T> {
4781 public:
4782 template <typename U>
4783 explicit BasicResult( BasicResult<U> const& other ):
4784 ResultValueBase<T>( other.type() ),
4785 m_errorMessage( other.errorMessage() ) {
4786 assert( type() != ResultType::Ok );
4787 }
4788
4789 template <typename U>
4790 static auto ok( U const& value ) -> BasicResult {
4791 return { ResultType::Ok, value };
4792 }
4793 static auto ok() -> BasicResult { return { ResultType::Ok }; }
4794 static auto logicError( std::string&& message )
4795 -> BasicResult {
4796 return { ResultType::LogicError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4797 }
4798 static auto runtimeError( std::string&& message )
4799 -> BasicResult {
4800 return { ResultType::RuntimeError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4801 }
4802
4803 explicit operator bool() const {
4804 return m_type == ResultType::Ok;
4805 }
4806 auto type() const -> ResultType { return m_type; }
4807 auto errorMessage() const -> std::string const& {
4808 return m_errorMessage;
4809 }
4810
4811 protected:
4812 void enforceOk() const override {
4813
4814 // Errors shouldn't reach this point, but if they do
4815 // the actual error message will be in m_errorMessage
4816 assert( m_type != ResultType::LogicError );
4817 assert( m_type != ResultType::RuntimeError );
4818 if ( m_type != ResultType::Ok )
4819 std::abort();
4820 }
4821
4822 std::string
4823 m_errorMessage; // Only populated if resultType is an error
4824
4825 BasicResult( ResultType type,
4826 std::string&& message ):
4827 ResultValueBase<T>( type ), m_errorMessage( CATCH_MOVE(message) ) {
4828 assert( m_type != ResultType::Ok );
4829 }
4830
4831 using ResultValueBase<T>::ResultValueBase;
4832 using ResultBase::m_type;
4833 };
4834
4835 class ParseState {
4836 public:
4837 ParseState( ParseResultType type,
4838 TokenStream const& remainingTokens );
4839
4840 ParseResultType type() const { return m_type; }
4841 TokenStream const& remainingTokens() const {
4842 return m_remainingTokens;
4843 }
4844
4845 private:
4846 ParseResultType m_type;
4847 TokenStream m_remainingTokens;
4848 };

4850 using Result = BasicResult<void>;
4851 using ParserResult = BasicResult<ParseResultType>;
4852 using InternalParseResult = BasicResult<ParseState>;
4853
4854 struct HelpColumns {
4855 std::string left;
4856 std::string right;
4857 };
4858
4859 template <typename T>
4860 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, T& target ) {
4861 std::stringstream ss( source );
4862 ss >> target;
4863 if ( ss.fail() ) {
4864 return ParserResult::runtimeError(
4865 "Unable to convert '" + source +
4866 "' to destination type" );
4867 } else {
4868 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4869 }
4870 }
4871 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source,
4872 std::string& target );
4873 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, bool& target );
4874
4875#ifdef CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4876 template <typename T>
4877 auto convertInto( std::string const& source,
4878 CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE<T>& target )
4879 -> ParserResult {
4880 T temp;
4881 auto result = convertInto( source, temp );
4882 if ( result )
4883 target = CATCH_MOVE( temp );
4884 return result;
4885 }
4886#endif // CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4887
4888 struct BoundRef : Catch::Detail::NonCopyable {
4889 virtual ~BoundRef() = default;
4890 virtual bool isContainer() const;
4891 virtual bool isFlag() const;
4892 };
4893 struct BoundValueRefBase : BoundRef {
4894 virtual auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4895 -> ParserResult = 0;
4896 };
4897 struct BoundFlagRefBase : BoundRef {
4898 virtual auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult = 0;
4899 bool isFlag() const override;
4900 };
4901
4902 template <typename T> struct BoundValueRef : BoundValueRefBase {
4903 T& m_ref;
4904
4905 explicit BoundValueRef( T& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4906
4907 ParserResult setValue( std::string const& arg ) override {
4908 return convertInto( arg, m_ref );
4909 }
4910 };
4911
4912 template <typename T>
4913 struct BoundValueRef<std::vector<T>> : BoundValueRefBase {
4914 std::vector<T>& m_ref;
4915
4916 explicit BoundValueRef( std::vector<T>& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4917
4918 auto isContainer() const -> bool override { return true; }
4919
4920 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4921 -> ParserResult override {
4922 T temp;
4923 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4924 if ( result )
4925 m_ref.push_back( temp );
4926 return result;
4927 }
4928 };
4929
4930 struct BoundFlagRef : BoundFlagRefBase {
4931 bool& m_ref;
4932
4933 explicit BoundFlagRef( bool& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4934
4935 ParserResult setFlag( bool flag ) override;
4936 };
4937
4938 template <typename ReturnType> struct LambdaInvoker {
4939 static_assert(
4940 std::is_same<ReturnType, ParserResult>::value,
4941 "Lambda must return void or clara::ParserResult" );
4942
4943 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4944 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4945 -> ParserResult {
4946 return lambda( arg );
4947 }
4948 };
4949
4950 template <> struct LambdaInvoker<void> {
4951 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4952 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4953 -> ParserResult {
4954 lambda( arg );
4955 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4956 }
4957 };
4958
4959 template <typename ArgType, typename L>
4960 auto invokeLambda( L const& lambda, std::string const& arg )
4961 -> ParserResult {
4962 ArgType temp{};
4963 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4964 return !result ? result
4965 : LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4966 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( lambda, temp );
4967 }
4968
4969 template <typename L> struct BoundLambda : BoundValueRefBase {
4970 L m_lambda;
4971
4972 static_assert(
4973 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4974 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4975 explicit BoundLambda( L const& lambda ): m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4976
4977 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4978 -> ParserResult override {
4979 return invokeLambda<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType>(
4980 m_lambda, arg );
4981 }
4982 };
4983
4984 template <typename L> struct BoundManyLambda : BoundLambda<L> {
4985 explicit BoundManyLambda( L const& lambda ): BoundLambda<L>( lambda ) {}
4986 bool isContainer() const override { return true; }
4987 };
4988
4989 template <typename L> struct BoundFlagLambda : BoundFlagRefBase {
4990 L m_lambda;
4991
4992 static_assert(
4993 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4994 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4995 static_assert(
4996 std::is_same<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType,
4997 bool>::value,
4998 "flags must be boolean" );
4999
5000 explicit BoundFlagLambda( L const& lambda ):
5001 m_lambda( lambda ) {}
5002
5003 auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult override {
5004 return LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
5005 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( m_lambda, flag );
5006 }
5007 };
5008
5009 enum class Optionality { Optional, Required };
5010
5011 class ParserBase {
5012 public:
5013 virtual ~ParserBase() = default;
5014 virtual auto validate() const -> Result { return Result::ok(); }
5015 virtual auto parse( std::string const& exeName,
5016 TokenStream const& tokens ) const
5017 -> InternalParseResult = 0;
5018 virtual size_t cardinality() const;
5019
5020 InternalParseResult parse( Args const& args ) const;
5021 };
5022
5023 template <typename DerivedT>
5024 class ComposableParserImpl : public ParserBase {
5025 public:
5026 template <typename T>
5027 auto operator|( T const& other ) const -> Parser;
5028 };
5029
5030 // Common code and state for Args and Opts
5031 template <typename DerivedT>
5032 class ParserRefImpl : public ComposableParserImpl<DerivedT> {
5033 protected:
5034 Optionality m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
5035 std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> m_ref;
5036 std::string m_hint;
5037 std::string m_description;
5038
5039 explicit ParserRefImpl( std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> const& ref ):
5040 m_ref( ref ) {}
5041
5042 public:
5043 template <typename LambdaT>
5044 ParserRefImpl( accept_many_t,
5045 LambdaT const& ref,
5046 std::string const& hint ):
5047 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundManyLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
5048 m_hint( hint ) {}
5049
5050 template <typename T,
5051 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
5052 !Detail::is_unary_function<T>::value>>
5053 ParserRefImpl( T& ref, std::string const& hint ):
5054 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundValueRef<T>>( ref ) ),
5055 m_hint( hint ) {}
5056
5057 template <typename LambdaT,
5058 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
5059 Detail::is_unary_function<LambdaT>::value>>
5060 ParserRefImpl( LambdaT const& ref, std::string const& hint ):
5061 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
5062 m_hint( hint ) {}
5063
5064 auto operator()( std::string const& description ) -> DerivedT& {
5065 m_description = description;
5066 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
5067 }
5068
5069 auto optional() -> DerivedT& {
5070 m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
5071 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
5072 }
5073
5074 auto required() -> DerivedT& {
5075 m_optionality = Optionality::Required;
5076 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
5077 }
5078
5079 auto isOptional() const -> bool {
5080 return m_optionality == Optionality::Optional;
5081 }
5082
5083 auto cardinality() const -> size_t override {
5084 if ( m_ref->isContainer() )
5085 return 0;
5086 else
5087 return 1;
5088 }
5089
5090 std::string const& hint() const { return m_hint; }
5091 };
5092
5093 } // namespace detail
5094

5184
5185 public:

5188 m_exeName = exeName;
5189 return *this;
5190 }

5193 m_args.push_back(arg);
5194 return *this;
5195 }
5196
5197 auto operator|=(Opt const& opt) -> Parser& {
5198 m_options.push_back(opt);
5199 return *this;
5200 }
5201
5202 Parser& operator|=(Parser const& other);
5203
5204 template <typename T>
5205 auto operator|(T const& other) const -> Parser {
5206 return Parser(*this) |= other;
5207 }
5208
5209 std::vector<Detail::HelpColumns> getHelpColumns() const;
5210
5211 void writeToStream(std::ostream& os) const;
5212
5213 friend auto operator<<(std::ostream& os, Parser const& parser)
5214 -> std::ostream& {
5215 parser.writeToStream(os);
5216 return os;
5217 }
5218
5219 Detail::Result validate() const override;
5220
5221 using ParserBase::parse;
5222 Detail::InternalParseResult
5223 parse(std::string const& exeName,
5224 Detail::TokenStream const& tokens) const override;
5225 };

5227 // Transport for raw args (copied from main args, or supplied via
5228 // init list for testing)
5229 class Args {
5230 friend Detail::TokenStream;

5302 if (m_startupExceptions)
5303 return 1;

5305 if (returnCode == 0)
5306 returnCode = run();
5307 return returnCode;
5308 }

5408#ifndef CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED
5409#define CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED
5410
5411
5412#include <type_traits>
5413
5414namespace Catch {
5415 namespace Detail {
5416
5417#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5418# pragma GCC diagnostic push
5419 // GCC likes to complain about comparing bool with 0, in the decltype()
5420 // that defines the comparable traits below.
5421# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wbool-compare"
5422 // "ordered comparison of pointer with integer zero" same as above,
5423 // but it does not have a separate warning flag to suppress
5424# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wextra"
5425 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5426 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5427# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5428#endif
5429
5430#if defined( __clang__ )
5431# pragma clang diagnostic push
5432 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5433 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5434# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5435#endif
5436
5437#define CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( id, op ) \
5438 template <typename, typename, typename = void> \
5439 struct is_##id##_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5440 template <typename T, typename U> \
5441 struct is_##id##_comparable< \
5442 T, \
5443 U, \
5444 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op std::declval<U>() )>> \
5445 : std::true_type {}; \
5446 template <typename, typename = void> \
5447 struct is_##id##_0_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5448 template <typename T> \
5449 struct is_##id##_0_comparable<T, \
5450 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op 0 )>> \
5451 : std::true_type {};
5452
5453 // We need all 6 pre-spaceship comparison ops: <, <=, >, >=, ==, !=
5454 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( lt, < )
5455 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( le, <= )
5456 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( gt, > )
5457 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ge, >= )
5458 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( eq, == )
5459 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ne, != )
5460
5461#undef CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT
5462
5463#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5464# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5465#endif
5466#if defined( __clang__ )
5467# pragma clang diagnostic pop
5468#endif
5469
5470
5471 } // namespace Detail
5472} // namespace Catch
5473
5474#endif // CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED

5480#include <type_traits>

5482namespace Catch {
5483namespace Detail {
5484
5485#if defined( __cpp_lib_logical_traits ) && __cpp_lib_logical_traits >= 201510
5486
5487 using std::conjunction;
5488 using std::disjunction;
5489 using std::negation;
5490
5491#else
5492
5493 template <class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
5494 template <class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5495 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5496 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...>
5497 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), conjunction<Bn...>, B1> {};
5498
5499 template <class...> struct disjunction : std::false_type {};
5500 template <class B1> struct disjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5501 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5502 struct disjunction<B1, Bn...>
5503 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), B1, disjunction<Bn...>> {};
5504
5505 template <class B>
5506 struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, !bool(B::value)> {};
5507
5508#endif

5510} // namespace Detail
