5538 struct always_false : std::false_type {};
5539
5540 class ITransientExpression {
5541 bool m_isBinaryExpression;
5542 bool m_result;
5543
5544 public:
5545 auto isBinaryExpression() const -> bool { return m_isBinaryExpression; }
5546 auto getResult() const -> bool { return m_result; }
5547 virtual void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const = 0;
5548
5549 ITransientExpression( bool isBinaryExpression, bool result )
5550 : m_isBinaryExpression( isBinaryExpression ),
5551 m_result( result )
5552 {}
5553
5554 ITransientExpression() = default;
5555 ITransientExpression(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
5556 ITransientExpression& operator=(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
5557
5558 // We don't actually need a virtual destructor, but many static analysers
5559 // complain if it's not here :-(
5560 virtual ~ITransientExpression(); // = default;
5561
5562 friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out, ITransientExpression const& expr) {
5563 expr.streamReconstructedExpression(out);
5564 return out;
5565 }
5566 };
5567
5568 void formatReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os, std::string const& lhs, StringRef op, std::string const& rhs );
5569
5570 template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
5571 class BinaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
5572 LhsT m_lhs;
5573 StringRef m_op;
5574 RhsT m_rhs;
5575
5576 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
5577 formatReconstructedExpression
5578 ( os, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs ), m_op, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_rhs ) );
5579 }
5580
5581 public:
5582 BinaryExpr( bool comparisonResult, LhsT lhs, StringRef op, RhsT rhs )
5583 : ITransientExpression{ true, comparisonResult },
5584 m_lhs( lhs ),
5585 m_op( op ),
5586 m_rhs( rhs )
5587 {}
5588
5589 template<typename T>
5590 auto operator && ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5591 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5592 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5593 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5594 }
5595
5596 template<typename T>
5597 auto operator || ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5598 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5599 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5600 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5601 }
5602
5603 template<typename T>
5604 auto operator == ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5605 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5606 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5607 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5608 }
5609
5610 template<typename T>
5611 auto operator != ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5612 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5613 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5614 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5615 }
5616
5617 template<typename T>
5618 auto operator > ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5619 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5620 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5621 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5622 }
5623
5624 template<typename T>
5625 auto operator < ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5626 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5627 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5628 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5629 }
5630
5631 template<typename T>
5632 auto operator >= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5633 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5634 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5635 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5636 }
5637
5638 template<typename T>
5639 auto operator <= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5640 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5641 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5642 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5643 }
5644 };
5645
5646 template<typename LhsT>
5647 class UnaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
5648 LhsT m_lhs;
5649
5650 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
5651 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs );
5652 }
5653
5654 public:
5655 explicit UnaryExpr( LhsT lhs )
5656 : ITransientExpression{ false, static_cast<bool>(lhs) },
5657 m_lhs( lhs )
5658 {}
5659 };

5661
5662 template<typename LhsT>
5663 class ExprLhs {
5664 LhsT m_lhs;
5665 public:
5666 explicit ExprLhs( LhsT lhs ) : m_lhs( lhs ) {}
5667
5668#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( id, op ) \
5669 template <typename RhsT> \
5670 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5671 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5672 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5673 Detail::negation<std::is_arithmetic< \
5674 std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>>>::value, \
5675 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5676 return { \
5677 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5678 } \
5679 template <typename RhsT> \
5680 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5681 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5682 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5683 std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>>::value, \
5684 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5685 return { \
5686 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5687 } \
5688 template <typename RhsT> \
5689 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5690 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5691 Detail::conjunction< \
5692 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5693 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<LhsT>, \
5694 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5695 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<RhsT, int>, \
5696 std::is_same<RhsT, long>>>::value, \
5697 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5698 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5699 return { \
5700 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5701 } \
5702 template <typename RhsT> \
5703 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5704 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5705 Detail::conjunction< \
5706 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5707 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5708 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5709 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<LhsT, int>, \
5710 std::is_same<LhsT, long>>>::value, \
5711 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5712 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5713 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5714 }
5715
5716 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( eq, == )
5717 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( ne, != )
5718
5719 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR
5720
5721#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( id, op ) \
5722 template <typename RhsT> \
5723 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5724 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5725 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5726 Detail::negation<std::is_arithmetic< \
5727 std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>>>::value, \
5728 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5729 return { \
5730 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5731 } \
5732 template <typename RhsT> \
5733 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5734 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5735 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5736 std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>>::value, \
5737 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5738 return { \
5739 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5740 } \
5741 template <typename RhsT> \
5742 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5743 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5744 Detail::conjunction< \
5745 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5746 Detail::is_##id##_0_comparable<LhsT>, \
5747 std::is_same<RhsT, int>>::value, \
5748 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5749 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5750 return { \
5751 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5752 } \
5753 template <typename RhsT> \
5754 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5755 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5756 Detail::conjunction< \
5757 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5758 Detail::is_##id##_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5759 std::is_same<LhsT, int>>::value, \
5760 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5761 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5762 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5763 }
5764
5765 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( lt, < )
5766 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( le, <= )
5767 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( gt, > )
5768 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( ge, >= )
5769
5770 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR
5771
5772
5773#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR( op ) \
5774 template <typename RhsT> \
5775 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5776 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5777 !std::is_arithmetic<std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>::value, \
5778 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5779 return { \
5780 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5781 } \
5782 template <typename RhsT> \
5783 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5784 ->std::enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>::value, \
5785 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5786 return { \
5787 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5788 }
5789
5790 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(|)
5791 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(&)
5792 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(^)
5793
5794 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR
5795
5796 template<typename RhsT>
5797 friend auto operator && ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5798 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5799 "operator&& is not supported inside assertions, "
5800 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5801 }
5802
5803 template<typename RhsT>
5804 friend auto operator || ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5805 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5806 "operator|| is not supported inside assertions, "
5807 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5808 }
5809
5810 auto makeUnaryExpr() const -> UnaryExpr<LhsT> {
5811 return UnaryExpr<LhsT>{ m_lhs };
5812 }
5813 };
5814
5815 struct Decomposer {
5816 template<typename T, std::enable_if_t<!std::is_arithmetic<std::remove_reference_t<T>>::value, int> = 0>
5817 friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T && lhs ) -> ExprLhs<T const&> {
5818 return ExprLhs<const T&>{ lhs };
5819 }
5820
5821 template<typename T, std::enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<T>::value, int> = 0>
5822 friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T value ) -> ExprLhs<T> {
5823 return ExprLhs<T>{ value };
5824 }
5825 };

5852 class AssertionHandler {

5854 AssertionReaction m_reaction;

5856 IResultCapture& m_resultCapture;
5857
5858 public:
5859 AssertionHandler
5860 ( StringRef macroName,
5861 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo,
5862 StringRef capturedExpression,
5863 ResultDisposition::Flags resultDisposition );
5864 ~AssertionHandler() {
5865 if ( !m_completed ) {
5866 m_resultCapture.handleIncomplete( m_assertionInfo );
5867 }
5868 }
5869
5870
5871 template<typename T>
5872 void handleExpr( ExprLhs<T> const& expr ) {
5873 handleExpr( expr.makeUnaryExpr() );
5874 }
5875 void handleExpr( ITransientExpression const& expr );
5876
5877 void handleMessage(ResultWas::OfType resultType, StringRef message);
5878
5879 void handleExceptionThrownAsExpected();
5880 void handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown();
5881 void handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected();
5882 void handleThrowingCallSkipped();
5883 void handleUnexpectedInflightException();
5884
5885 void complete();
5886 void setCompleted();
5887
5888 // query
5889 auto allowThrows() const -> bool;
5890 };
5891
5892 void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, std::string const& str );
5893
5894} // namespace Catch
5895
5896#endif // CATCH_ASSERTION_HANDLER_HPP_INCLUDED

5898// We need this suppression to leak, because it took until GCC 10
5899// for the front end to handle local suppression via _Pragma properly
5900#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && !defined(__ICC) && __GNUC__ <= 9
5901 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wparentheses"
5902#endif

5904#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
5905
5906#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION)
5907 #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) #__VA_ARGS__
5908#else
5909 #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) "Disabled by CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION"
5910#endif

5912#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE) || defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
5913
5915// Another way to speed-up compilation is to omit local try-catch for REQUIRE*
5916// macros.
5917#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY
5918#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( capturer )
5919
5920#else // CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE
5921
5922#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY try
5923#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( handler ) catch(...) { handler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); }
5924
5925#endif
5926
5927#define INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( handler ) handler.complete();
5928
5930#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5931 do { /* NOLINT(bugprone-infinite-loop) */ \
5932 /* The expression should not be evaluated, but warnings should hopefully be checked */ \
5933 CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(__VA_ARGS__); \
5934 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5935 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
5936 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5937 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
5938 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::Decomposer() <= __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5939 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5940 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5941 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5942 } while( (void)0, (false) && static_cast<const bool&>( !!(__VA_ARGS__) ) ) // the expression here is never evaluated at runtime but it forces the compiler to give it a look
5943 // The double negation silences MSVC's C4800 warning, the static_cast forces short-circuit evaluation if the type has overloaded &&.
5944
5946#define INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5947 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5948 if( Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5949
5951#define INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5952 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5953 if( !Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5954
5956#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5957 do { \
5958 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5959 try { \
5960 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5961 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5962 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5963 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5964 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected(); \
5965 } \
5966 catch( ... ) { \
5967 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5968 } \
5969 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5970 } while( false )
5971
5973#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5974 do { \
5975 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition); \
5976 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5977 try { \
5978 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5979 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5980 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5981 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5982 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5983 } \
5984 catch( ... ) { \
5985 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5986 } \
5987 else \
5988 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5989 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5990 } while( false )
5991
5993#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, expr ) \
5994 do { \
5995 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(expr) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType), resultDisposition ); \
5996 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5997 try { \
5998 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5999 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
6000 static_cast<void>(expr); \
6001 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6002 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
6003 } \
6004 catch( exceptionType const& ) { \
6005 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
6006 } \
6007 catch( ... ) { \
6008 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
6009 } \
6010 else \
6011 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
6012 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
6013 } while( false )
6014
6015
6016
6018// Although this is matcher-based, it can be used with just a string
6019#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_STR_MATCHES( macroName, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
6020 do { \
6021 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
6022 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
6023 try { \
6024 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6025 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
6026 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
6027 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6028 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
6029 } \
6030 catch( ... ) { \
6031 Catch::handleExceptionMatchExpr( catchAssertionHandler, matcher ); \
6032 } \
6033 else \
6034 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
6035 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
6036 } while( false )
6037
6038#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE

6174template<typename C>
6175class TestInvokerAsMethod : public ITestInvoker {
6176 void (C::*m_testAsMethod)();
6177public:
6178 TestInvokerAsMethod( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) noexcept : m_testAsMethod( testAsMethod ) {}
6179
6180 void invoke() const override {
6181 C obj;
6182 (obj.*m_testAsMethod)();
6183 }
6184};
6185
6186Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void(*testAsFunction)() );
6187
6188template<typename C>
6189Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) {
6190 return Detail::make_unique<TestInvokerAsMethod<C>>( testAsMethod );
6191}
6192
6193struct NameAndTags {
6194 constexpr NameAndTags( StringRef name_ = StringRef(),
6195 StringRef tags_ = StringRef() ) noexcept:
6196 name( name_ ), tags( tags_ ) {}
6197 StringRef name;
6198 StringRef tags;
6199};
6200
6201struct AutoReg : Detail::NonCopyable {
6202 AutoReg( Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> invoker, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, StringRef classOrMethod, NameAndTags const& nameAndTags ) noexcept;
6203};

6269// All of our user-facing macros support configuration toggle, that

6517#define CATCH_REC_GET_END1(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END2
6518#define CATCH_REC_GET_END(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END1
6519#define CATCH_REC_NEXT0(test, next, ...) next CATCH_REC_OUT
6520#define CATCH_REC_NEXT1(test, next) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT0 ) ( test, next, 0)
6521#define CATCH_REC_NEXT(test, next) CATCH_REC_NEXT1(CATCH_REC_GET_END test, next)

6523#define CATCH_REC_LIST0(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6524#define CATCH_REC_LIST1(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6525#define CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, x, peek, ...) f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6526
6527#define CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6528#define CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6529#define CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6530
6531// Applies the function macro `f` to each of the remaining parameters, inserts commas between the results,
6532// and passes userdata as the first parameter to each invocation,
6533// e.g. CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, x, a, b, c) evaluates to f(x, a), f(x, b), f(x, c)
6534#define CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, userdata, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))
6535
6536#define CATCH_REC_LIST(f, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))

6577#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN\
6578 template<typename...> struct TypeList {};\
6579 template<typename...Ts>\
6580 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TypeList<Ts...> { return {}; }\
6581 template<template<typename...> class...> struct TemplateTypeList{};\
6582 template<template<typename...> class...Cs>\
6583 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; }\
6584 template<typename...>\
6585 struct append;\
6586 template<typename...>\
6587 struct rewrap;\
6588 template<template<typename...> class, typename...>\
6589 struct create;\
6590 template<template<typename...> class, typename>\
6591 struct convert;\
6592 \
6593 template<typename T> \
6594 struct append<T> { using type = T; };\
6595 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, template<typename...> class L2, typename...E2, typename...Rest>\
6596 struct append<L1<E1...>, L2<E2...>, Rest...> { using type = typename append<L1<E1...,E2...>, Rest...>::type; };\
6597 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, typename...Rest>\
6598 struct append<L1<E1...>, TypeList<mpl_::na>, Rest...> { using type = L1<E1...>; };\
6599 \
6600 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, typename...elems>\
6601 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<elems...>> { using type = TypeList<Container<elems...>>; };\
6602 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, class...Elems, typename...Elements>\
6603 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<Elems...>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<Elems...>>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6604 \
6605 template<template <typename...> class Final, template< typename...> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
6606 struct create<Final, TemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };\
6607 template<template <typename...> class Final, template <typename...> class List, typename...Ts>\
6608 struct convert<Final, List<Ts...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>,TypeList<Ts>...>::type; };

6610#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_1(signature, ...)\
6611 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> struct Nttp{};\
6612 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6613 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> Nttp<__VA_ARGS__> { return {}; } \
6614 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...> struct NttpTemplateTypeList{};\
6615 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Cs>\
6616 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> NttpTemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; } \
6617 \
6618 template< template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class Container, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class List, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6619 struct rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, List<__VA_ARGS__>> { using type = TypeList<Container<__VA_ARGS__>>; };\
6620 template< template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class Container, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class List, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature), typename...Elements>\
6621 struct rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, List<__VA_ARGS__>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<__VA_ARGS__>>, typename rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6622 template<template <typename...> class Final, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
6623 struct create<Final, NttpTemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };

6648#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_REGISTER(TestFunc, signature, ...)\
6649 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6650 void reg_test(Nttp<__VA_ARGS__>, Catch::NameAndTags nameAndTags)\

6770 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6771 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \
6772 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_WARNINGS \

6778 INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN\

6780 INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_REG_GEN(TestFunc,INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature))\
6781 template<typename...Types> \
6782 struct TestName{\
6783 TestName(){\
6784 size_t index = 0; \
6785 constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, __VA_ARGS__)}; /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays,modernize-avoid-c-arrays,hicpp-avoid-c-arrays) */\
6786 using expander = size_t[]; /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays,modernize-avoid-c-arrays,hicpp-avoid-c-arrays) */\
6787 (void)expander{(reg_test(Types{}, Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index]), Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */ \
6788 }\
6789 };\

6815 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEMPLATE_PRODUCT_TEST_CASE2(TestName, TestFuncName, Name, Tags, Signature, TmplTypes, TypesList) \
6816 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6817 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6818 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \
6819 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_WARNINGS \
6820 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
6821 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_COMMA_WARNINGS \
6822 template<typename TestType> static void TestFuncName(); \
6823 namespace {\
6824 namespace INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_NAMESPACE(TestName) { \
6825 INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN \
6826 INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_GEN(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature)) \
6827 template<typename... Types> \
6828 struct TestName { \
6829 void reg_tests() { \
6830 size_t index = 0; \
6831 using expander = size_t[]; \
6832 constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes))};\
6833 constexpr char const* types_list[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))};\
6834 constexpr auto num_types = sizeof(types_list) / sizeof(types_list[0]);\
6835 (void)expander{(Catch::AutoReg( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestFuncName<Types> ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index / num_types]) + '<' + std::string(types_list[index % num_types]) + '>', Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */\
6836 } \
6837 }; \
6838 static int INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( globalRegistrar ) = [](){ \
6839 using TestInit = typename create<TestName, decltype(get_wrapper<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes)>()), TypeList<INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_TYPE_LISTS_FROM_TYPES(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))>>::type; \
6840 TestInit t; \
6841 t.reg_tests(); \
6842 return 0; \
6843 }(); \
6844 } \
6845 } \
6846 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6847 template<typename TestType> \
6848 static void TestFuncName()

6851 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEMPLATE_PRODUCT_TEST_CASE(Name, Tags, ...)\

6916 using expander = size_t[];\

6945 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEMPLATE_PRODUCT_TEST_CASE_METHOD_2(TestNameClass, TestName, ClassName, Name, Tags, Signature, TmplTypes, TypesList)\
6946 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6947 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6948 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \

6953 void test();\
6954 };\
6955 namespace {\
6956 namespace INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_NAMESPACE(TestNameClass) {\
6957 INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN \
6958 INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_GEN(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature))\
6959 template<typename...Types>\
6960 struct TestNameClass{\
6961 void reg_tests(){\
6962 std::size_t index = 0;\
6963 using expander = std::size_t[];\
6964 constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes))};\
6965 constexpr char const* types_list[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))};\
6966 constexpr auto num_types = sizeof(types_list) / sizeof(types_list[0]);\
6967 (void)expander{(Catch::AutoReg( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestName<Types>::test ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, #ClassName, Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index / num_types]) + '<' + std::string(types_list[index % num_types]) + '>', Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */ \
6968 }\
6969 };\
6970 static int INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( globalRegistrar ) = [](){\
6971 using TestInit = typename create<TestNameClass, decltype(get_wrapper<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes)>()), TypeList<INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_TYPE_LISTS_FROM_TYPES(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))>>::type;\
6972 TestInit t;\
6973 t.reg_tests();\
6974 return 0;\
6975 }(); \
6976 }\
6977 }\

6980 void TestName<TestType>::test()

7296namespace Catch {
7297
7298 class ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar {
7299 template<typename T>
7300 class ExceptionTranslator : public IExceptionTranslator {
7301 public:
7302
7303 ExceptionTranslator( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) )
7304 : m_translateFunction( translateFunction )
7305 {}
7306
7307 std::string translate( ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator it, ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator itEnd ) const override {
7308#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
7309 try {
7310 if( it == itEnd )
7311 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
7312 else
7313 return (*it)->translate( it+1, itEnd );
7314 }
7315 catch( T const& ex ) {
7316 return m_translateFunction( ex );
7317 }
7318#else
7319 return "You should never get here!";
7320#endif
7321 }
7322
7323 protected:
7324 std::string(*m_translateFunction)( T const& );
7325 };
7326
7327 public:
7328 template<typename T>
7329 ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) ) {
7330 getMutableRegistryHub().registerTranslator(
7331 Detail::make_unique<ExceptionTranslator<T>>(translateFunction)
7332 );
7333 }
7334 };
7335
7336} // namespace Catch

7339#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION2( translatorName, signature ) \
7340 static std::string translatorName( signature ); \
7341 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7342 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
7343 namespace{ Catch::ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionRegistrar )( &translatorName ); } \
7344 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7345 static std::string translatorName( signature )
7346
7347#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION2( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionTranslator ), signature )
7348
7349#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
7350 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION_NO_REG( translatorName, signature) \
7351 static std::string translatorName( signature )
7352#endif
7353
7354
7355// This macro is always prefixed
7356#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)

7556 template<typename T>
7557 class IGenerator : public GeneratorUntypedBase {
7558 std::string stringifyImpl() const override {
7559 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify( get() );
7560 }
7561
7562 public:
7563 ~IGenerator() override = default;
7564 IGenerator() = default;
7565 IGenerator(IGenerator const&) = default;
7566 IGenerator& operator=(IGenerator const&) = default;
7567
7568
7569 // Returns the current element of the generator
7570 //
7571 // \Precondition The generator is either freshly constructed,
7572 // or the last call to `next()` returned true
7573 virtual T const& get() const = 0;
7574 using type = T;
7575 };

7577 template <typename T>
7578 using GeneratorPtr = Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<IGenerator<T>>;
7579
7580 template <typename T>
7581 class GeneratorWrapper final {
7582 GeneratorPtr<T> m_generator;
7583 public:
7585 GeneratorWrapper(IGenerator<T>* generator):
7586 m_generator(generator) {}
7587 GeneratorWrapper(GeneratorPtr<T> generator):
7588 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)) {}
7589
7590 T const& get() const {
7591 return m_generator->get();
7592 }
7593 bool next() {
7594 return m_generator->countedNext();
7595 }
7596 };

7599 template<typename T>
7600 class SingleValueGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7601 T m_value;
7602 public:
7603 SingleValueGenerator(T const& value) :
7604 m_value(value)
7605 {}
7606 SingleValueGenerator(T&& value):
7607 m_value(CATCH_MOVE(value))
7608 {}
7609
7610 T const& get() const override {
7611 return m_value;
7612 }
7613 bool next() override {
7614 return false;
7615 }
7616 };

7618 template<typename T>
7619 class FixedValuesGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7620 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7621 "FixedValuesGenerator does not support bools because of std::vector<bool>"
7622 "specialization, use SingleValue Generator instead.");
7623 std::vector<T> m_values;
7624 size_t m_idx = 0;
7625 public:
7626 FixedValuesGenerator( std::initializer_list<T> values ) : m_values( values ) {}
7627
7628 T const& get() const override {
7629 return m_values[m_idx];
7630 }
7631 bool next() override {
7632 ++m_idx;
7633 return m_idx < m_values.size();
7634 }
7635 };

7637 template <typename T, typename DecayedT = std::decay_t<T>>
7638 GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT> value( T&& value ) {
7639 return GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT>(
7640 Catch::Detail::make_unique<SingleValueGenerator<DecayedT>>(
7641 CATCH_FORWARD( value ) ) );
7642 }
7643 template <typename T>
7644 GeneratorWrapper<T> values(std::initializer_list<T> values) {
7645 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FixedValuesGenerator<T>>(values));
7646 }
7647
7648 template<typename T>
7649 class Generators : public IGenerator<T> {
7650 std::vector<GeneratorWrapper<T>> m_generators;
7651 size_t m_current = 0;
7652
7653 void add_generator( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) {
7654 m_generators.emplace_back( CATCH_MOVE( generator ) );
7655 }
7656 void add_generator( T const& val ) {
7657 m_generators.emplace_back( value( val ) );
7658 }
7659 void add_generator( T&& val ) {
7660 m_generators.emplace_back( value( CATCH_MOVE( val ) ) );
7661 }
7662 template <typename U>
7663 std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<std::decay_t<U>, T>::value>
7664 add_generator( U&& val ) {
7665 add_generator( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) );
7666 }
7667
7668 template <typename U> void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator ) {
7669 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7670 }
7671
7672 template <typename U, typename... Gs>
7673 void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator, Gs&&... moreGenerators ) {
7674 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7675 add_generators( CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7676 }
7677
7678 public:
7679 template <typename... Gs>
7680 Generators(Gs &&... moreGenerators) {
7681 m_generators.reserve(sizeof...(Gs));
7682 add_generators(CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7683 }
7684
7685 T const& get() const override {
7686 return m_generators[m_current].get();
7687 }
7688
7689 bool next() override {
7690 if (m_current >= m_generators.size()) {
7691 return false;
7692 }
7693 const bool current_status = m_generators[m_current].next();
7694 if (!current_status) {
7695 ++m_current;
7696 }
7697 return m_current < m_generators.size();
7698 }
7699 };
7700
7701
7702 template <typename... Ts>
7703 GeneratorWrapper<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>>
7704 table( std::initializer_list<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>> tuples ) {
7705 return values<std::tuple<Ts...>>( tuples );
7706 }
7707
7708 // Tag type to signal that a generator sequence should convert arguments to a specific type
7709 template <typename T>
7710 struct as {};
7711
7712 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7713 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7714 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator), CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7715 }
7716 template<typename T>
7717 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) -> Generators<T> {
7718 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator));
7719 }
7720 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7721 auto makeGenerators( T&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<std::decay_t<T>> {
7722 return makeGenerators( value( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7723 }
7724 template<typename T, typename U, typename... Gs>
7725 auto makeGenerators( as<T>, U&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7726 return makeGenerators( value( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7727 }
7728
7729 IGeneratorTracker* acquireGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7730 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo );
7731 IGeneratorTracker* createGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7732 SourceLineInfo lineInfo,
7733 GeneratorBasePtr&& generator );
7734
7735 template<typename L>
7736 auto generate( StringRef generatorName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, L const& generatorExpression ) -> typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type {
7737 using UnderlyingType = typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type;
7738
7739 IGeneratorTracker* tracker = acquireGeneratorTracker( generatorName, lineInfo );
7740 // Creation of tracker is delayed after generator creation, so
7741 // that constructing generator can fail without breaking everything.
7742 if (!tracker) {
7743 tracker = createGeneratorTracker(
7744 generatorName,
7745 lineInfo,
7746 Catch::Detail::make_unique<Generators<UnderlyingType>>(
7747 generatorExpression() ) );
7748 }
7749
7750 auto const& generator = static_cast<IGenerator<UnderlyingType> const&>( *tracker->getGenerator() );
7751 return generator.get();
7752 }
7753
7754} // namespace Generators
7755} // namespace Catch

7758 Catch::Generators::generate( INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7759 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7760 [ ]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7761#define GENERATE_COPY( ... ) \
7762 Catch::Generators::generate( INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7763 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7764 [=]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7765#define GENERATE_REF( ... ) \
7766 Catch::Generators::generate( INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7767 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7768 [&]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)

7773#ifndef CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7774#define CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7775
7776
7777#include <cassert>
7778
7779namespace Catch {
7780namespace Generators {
7781
7782 template <typename T>
7783 class TakeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7784 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7785 size_t m_returned = 0;
7786 size_t m_target;
7787 public:
7788 TakeGenerator(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7789 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7790 m_target(target)
7791 {
7792 assert(target != 0 && "Empty generators are not allowed");
7793 }
7794 T const& get() const override {
7795 return m_generator.get();
7796 }
7797 bool next() override {
7798 ++m_returned;
7799 if (m_returned >= m_target) {
7800 return false;
7801 }
7802
7803 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7804 // If the underlying generator does not contain enough values
7805 // then we cut short as well
7806 if (!success) {
7807 m_returned = m_target;
7808 }
7809 return success;
7810 }
7811 };
7812
7813 template <typename T>
7814 GeneratorWrapper<T> take(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7815 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<TakeGenerator<T>>(target, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7816 }
7817
7818
7819 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7820 class FilterGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7821 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7822 Predicate m_predicate;
7823 public:
7824 template <typename P = Predicate>
7825 FilterGenerator(P&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7826 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7827 m_predicate(CATCH_FORWARD(pred))
7828 {
7829 if (!m_predicate(m_generator.get())) {
7830 // It might happen that there are no values that pass the
7831 // filter. In that case we throw an exception.
7832 auto has_initial_value = next();
7833 if (!has_initial_value) {
7834 Detail::throw_generator_exception("No valid value found in filtered generator");
7835 }
7836 }
7837 }
7838
7839 T const& get() const override {
7840 return m_generator.get();
7841 }
7842
7843 bool next() override {
7844 bool success = m_generator.next();
7845 if (!success) {
7846 return false;
7847 }
7848 while (!m_predicate(m_generator.get()) && (success = m_generator.next()) == true);
7849 return success;
7850 }
7851 };
7852
7853
7854 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7855 GeneratorWrapper<T> filter(Predicate&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7856 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FilterGenerator<T, Predicate>>(CATCH_FORWARD(pred), CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7857 }
7858
7859 template <typename T>
7860 class RepeatGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7861 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7862 "RepeatGenerator currently does not support bools"
7863 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
7864 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7865 mutable std::vector<T> m_returned;
7866 size_t m_target_repeats;
7867 size_t m_current_repeat = 0;
7868 size_t m_repeat_index = 0;
7869 public:
7870 RepeatGenerator(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7871 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7872 m_target_repeats(repeats)
7873 {
7874 assert(m_target_repeats > 0 && "Repeat generator must repeat at least once");
7875 }
7876
7877 T const& get() const override {
7878 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7879 m_returned.push_back(m_generator.get());
7880 return m_returned.back();
7881 }
7882 return m_returned[m_repeat_index];
7883 }
7884
7885 bool next() override {
7886 // There are 2 basic cases:
7887 // 1) We are still reading the generator
7888 // 2) We are reading our own cache
7889
7890 // In the first case, we need to poke the underlying generator.
7891 // If it happily moves, we are left in that state, otherwise it is time to start reading from our cache
7892 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7893 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7894 if (!success) {
7895 ++m_current_repeat;
7896 }
7897 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7898 }
7899
7900 // In the second case, we need to move indices forward and check that we haven't run up against the end
7901 ++m_repeat_index;
7902 if (m_repeat_index == m_returned.size()) {
7903 m_repeat_index = 0;
7904 ++m_current_repeat;
7905 }
7906 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7907 }
7908 };
7909
7910 template <typename T>
7911 GeneratorWrapper<T> repeat(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7912 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RepeatGenerator<T>>(repeats, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7913 }
7914
7915 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7916 class MapGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7917 // TBD: provide static assert for mapping function, for friendly error message
7918 GeneratorWrapper<U> m_generator;
7919 Func m_function;
7920 // To avoid returning dangling reference, we have to save the values
7921 T m_cache;
7922 public:
7923 template <typename F2 = Func>
7924 MapGenerator(F2&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) :
7925 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7926 m_function(CATCH_FORWARD(function)),
7927 m_cache(m_function(m_generator.get()))
7928 {}
7929
7930 T const& get() const override {
7931 return m_cache;
7932 }
7933 bool next() override {
7934 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7935 if (success) {
7936 m_cache = m_function(m_generator.get());
7937 }
7938 return success;
7939 }
7940 };
7941
7942 template <typename Func, typename U, typename T = FunctionReturnType<Func, U>>
7943 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
7944 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7945 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7946 );
7947 }
7948
7949 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7950 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
7951 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7952 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7953 );
7954 }
7955
7956 template <typename T>
7957 class ChunkGenerator final : public IGenerator<std::vector<T>> {
7958 std::vector<T> m_chunk;
7959 size_t m_chunk_size;
7960 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7961 bool m_used_up = false;
7962 public:
7963 ChunkGenerator(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T> generator) :
7964 m_chunk_size(size), m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7965 {
7966 m_chunk.reserve(m_chunk_size);
7967 if (m_chunk_size != 0) {
7968 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7969 for (size_t i = 1; i < m_chunk_size; ++i) {
7970 if (!m_generator.next()) {
7971 Detail::throw_generator_exception("Not enough values to initialize the first chunk");
7972 }
7973 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7974 }
7975 }
7976 }
7977 std::vector<T> const& get() const override {
7978 return m_chunk;
7979 }
7980 bool next() override {
7981 m_chunk.clear();
7982 for (size_t idx = 0; idx < m_chunk_size; ++idx) {
7983 if (!m_generator.next()) {
7984 return false;
7985 }
7986 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7987 }
7988 return true;
7989 }
7990 };
7991
7992 template <typename T>
7993 GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>> chunk(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7994 return GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>>(
7995 Catch::Detail::make_unique<ChunkGenerator<T>>(size, CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7996 );
7997 }
7998
7999} // namespace Generators
8000} // namespace Catch

8011#ifndef CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
8012#define CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
8013
8014#include <cstdint>
8015
8016namespace Catch {
8017
8018 // This is a simple implementation of C++11 Uniform Random Number
8019 // Generator. It does not provide all operators, because Catch2
8020 // does not use it, but it should behave as expected inside stdlib's
8021 // distributions.
8022 // The implementation is based on the PCG family (http://pcg-random.org)
8023 class SimplePcg32 {
8024 using state_type = std::uint64_t;
8025 public:
8026 using result_type = std::uint32_t;
8027 static constexpr result_type (min)() {
8028 return 0;
8029 }
8030 static constexpr result_type (max)() {
8031 return static_cast<result_type>(-1);
8032 }
8033
8034 // Provide some default initial state for the default constructor
8035 SimplePcg32():SimplePcg32(0xed743cc4U) {}
8036
8037 explicit SimplePcg32(result_type seed_);
8038
8039 void seed(result_type seed_);
8040 void discard(uint64_t skip);
8041
8042 result_type operator()();
8043
8044 private:
8045 friend bool operator==(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8046 friend bool operator!=(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8047
8048 // In theory we also need operator<< and operator>>
8049 // In practice we do not use them, so we will skip them for now
8050
8051
8052 std::uint64_t m_state;
8053 // This part of the state determines which "stream" of the numbers
8054 // is chosen -- we take it as a constant for Catch2, so we only
8055 // need to deal with seeding the main state.
8056 // Picked by reading 8 bytes from `/dev/random` :-)
8057 static const std::uint64_t s_inc = (0x13ed0cc53f939476ULL << 1ULL) | 1ULL;
8058 };
8059
8060} // end namespace Catch
8061
8062#endif // CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
8063
8064#include <random>
8065
8066namespace Catch {
8067namespace Generators {
8068namespace Detail {
8069 // Returns a suitable seed for a random floating generator based off
8070 // the primary internal rng. It does so by taking current value from
8071 // the rng and returning it as the seed.
8072 std::uint32_t getSeed();
8073}
8074
8075template <typename Float>
8076class RandomFloatingGenerator final : public IGenerator<Float> {
8077 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8078 std::uniform_real_distribution<Float> m_dist;
8079 Float m_current_number;
8080public:
8081 RandomFloatingGenerator( Float a, Float b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8082 m_rng(seed),
8083 m_dist(a, b) {
8084 static_cast<void>(next());
8085 }
8086
8087 Float const& get() const override {
8088 return m_current_number;
8089 }
8090 bool next() override {
8091 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8092 return true;
8093 }
8094};
8095
8096template <typename Integer>
8097class RandomIntegerGenerator final : public IGenerator<Integer> {
8098 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8099 std::uniform_int_distribution<Integer> m_dist;
8100 Integer m_current_number;
8101public:
8102 RandomIntegerGenerator( Integer a, Integer b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8103 m_rng(seed),
8104 m_dist(a, b) {
8105 static_cast<void>(next());
8106 }
8107
8108 Integer const& get() const override {
8109 return m_current_number;
8110 }
8111 bool next() override {
8112 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8113 return true;
8114 }
8115};
8116
8117template <typename T>
8118std::enable_if_t<std::is_integral<T>::value, GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8119random(T a, T b) {
8120 static_assert(
8121 !std::is_same<T, char>::value &&
8122 !std::is_same<T, int8_t>::value &&
8123 !std::is_same<T, uint8_t>::value &&
8124 !std::is_same<T, signed char>::value &&
8125 !std::is_same<T, unsigned char>::value &&
8126 !std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
8127 "The requested type is not supported by the underlying random distributions from std" );
8128 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8129 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomIntegerGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8130 );
8131}
8132
8133template <typename T>
8134std::enable_if_t<std::is_floating_point<T>::value,
8135GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8136random(T a, T b) {
8137 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8138 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomFloatingGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8139 );
8140}

8160
8161template <typename T>
8162class RangeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8163 T m_current;
8164 T m_end;
8165 T m_step;
8166 bool m_positive;
8167
8168public:
8169 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step):
8170 m_current(start),
8171 m_end(end),
8172 m_step(step),
8173 m_positive(m_step > T(0))
8174 {
8175 assert(m_current != m_end && "Range start and end cannot be equal");
8176 assert(m_step != T(0) && "Step size cannot be zero");
8177 assert(((m_positive && m_current <= m_end) || (!m_positive && m_current >= m_end)) && "Step moves away from end");
8178 }
8179
8180 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end):
8181 RangeGenerator(start, end, (start < end) ? T(1) : T(-1))
8182 {}
8183
8184 T const& get() const override {
8185 return m_current;
8186 }
8187
8188 bool next() override {
8189 m_current += m_step;
8190 return (m_positive) ? (m_current < m_end) : (m_current > m_end);
8191 }
8192};
8193
8194template <typename T>
8195GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step) {
8196 static_assert(std::is_arithmetic<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be numeric");
8197 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end, step));
8198}
8199
8200template <typename T>
8201GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end) {
8202 static_assert(std::is_integral<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be an integer");
8203 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end));
8204}
8205
8206
8207template <typename T>
8208class IteratorGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8209 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
8210 "IteratorGenerator currently does not support bools"
8211 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
8212
8213 std::vector<T> m_elems;
8214 size_t m_current = 0;
8215public:
8216 template <typename InputIterator, typename InputSentinel>
8217 IteratorGenerator(InputIterator first, InputSentinel last):m_elems(first, last) {
8218 if (m_elems.empty()) {
8219 Detail::throw_generator_exception("IteratorGenerator received no valid values");
8220 }
8221 }
8222
8223 T const& get() const override {
8224 return m_elems[m_current];
8225 }
8226
8227 bool next() override {
8228 ++m_current;
8229 return m_current != m_elems.size();
8230 }
8231};
8232
8233template <typename InputIterator,
8234 typename InputSentinel,
8235 typename ResultType = typename std::iterator_traits<InputIterator>::value_type>
8236GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(InputIterator from, InputSentinel to) {
8237 return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(from, to));
8238}
8239
8240template <typename Container,
8241 typename ResultType = typename Container::value_type>
8242GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(Container const& cnt) {
8243 return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(cnt.begin(), cnt.end()));
8244}

8481#include <cstddef>
8482#include <initializer_list>
8483
8484// We want a simple polyfill over `std::empty`, `std::size` and so on
8485// for C++14 or C++ libraries with incomplete support.
8486// We also have to handle that MSVC std lib will happily provide these
8487// under older standards.
8488#if defined(CATCH_CPP17_OR_GREATER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
8489
8490// We are already using this header either way, so there shouldn't
8491// be much additional overhead in including it to get the feature
8492// test macros
8493#include <string>
8494
8495# if !defined(__cpp_lib_nonmember_container_access)
8496# define CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
8497# endif
8498
8499#else
8500#define CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
8501#endif
8502
8503
8504
8505namespace Catch {
8506namespace Detail {
8507
8508#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
8509 template <typename Container>
8510 constexpr auto empty(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.empty()) {
8511 return cont.empty();
8512 }
8513 template <typename T, std::size_t N>
8514 constexpr bool empty(const T (&)[N]) noexcept {
8515 // GCC < 7 does not support the const T(&)[] parameter syntax
8516 // so we have to ignore the length explicitly
8517 (void)N;
8518 return false;
8519 }
8520 template <typename T>
8521 constexpr bool empty(std::initializer_list<T> list) noexcept {
8522 return list.size() > 0;
8523 }
8524
8525
8526 template <typename Container>
8527 constexpr auto size(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.size()) {
8528 return cont.size();
8529 }
8530 template <typename T, std::size_t N>
8531 constexpr std::size_t size(const T(&)[N]) noexcept {
8532 return N;
8533 }
8534#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
8535
8536} // end namespace Detail
8537} // end namespace Catch

8556#ifndef CATCH_DEBUGGER_HPP_INCLUDED
8557#define CATCH_DEBUGGER_HPP_INCLUDED

8560namespace Catch {
8561 bool isDebuggerActive();
8562}
8563
8564#ifdef CATCH_PLATFORM_MAC
8565
8566 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
8567 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3\n" : : ) /* NOLINT */
8568 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
8569 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd43e0000")
8570 #elif defined(__POWERPC__)
8571 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("li r0, 20\nsc\nnop\nli r0, 37\nli r4, 2\nsc\nnop\n" \
8572 : : : "memory","r0","r3","r4" ) /* NOLINT */
8573 #endif
8574
8575#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_IPHONE)
8576
8577 // use inline assembler
8578 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
8579 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3")
8580 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
8581 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd4200000")
8582 #elif defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
8583 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xe7f001f0")
8584 #elif defined(__arm__) && defined(__thumb__)
8585 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xde01")
8586 #endif
8587
8588#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX)
8589 // If we can use inline assembler, do it because this allows us to break
8590 // directly at the location of the failing check instead of breaking inside
8591 // raise() called from it, i.e. one stack frame below.
8592 #if defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386) || defined(__x86_64))
8593 #define CATCH_TRAP() asm volatile ("int $3") /* NOLINT */
8594 #else // Fall back to the generic way.
8595 #include <signal.h>
8596
8597 #define CATCH_TRAP() raise(SIGTRAP)
8598 #endif
8599#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
8600 #define CATCH_TRAP() __debugbreak()
8601#elif defined(__MINGW32__)
8602 extern "C" __declspec(dllimport) void __stdcall DebugBreak();
8603 #define CATCH_TRAP() DebugBreak()
8604#endif
8605
8606#ifndef CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER
8607 #ifdef CATCH_TRAP
8608 #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{ if( Catch::isDebuggerActive() ) { CATCH_TRAP(); } }()
8609 #else
8610 #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{}()
8611 #endif
8612#endif
8613
8614#endif // CATCH_DEBUGGER_HPP_INCLUDED

8627 void throw_exception(Ex const& e) {
8628 throw e;
8629 }
8630#else // ^^ Exceptions are enabled // Exceptions are disabled vv

8640 void throw_runtime_error(std::string const& msg);

8643
8644#define CATCH_MAKE_MSG(...) \
8645 (Catch::ReusableStringStream() << __VA_ARGS__).str()
8646
8647#define CATCH_INTERNAL_ERROR(...) \
8648 Catch::throw_logic_error(CATCH_MAKE_MSG( CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO << ": Internal Catch2 error: " << __VA_ARGS__))
8649
8650#define CATCH_ERROR(...) \
8651 Catch::throw_domain_error(CATCH_MAKE_MSG( __VA_ARGS__ ))
8652
8653#define CATCH_RUNTIME_ERROR(...) \
8654 Catch::throw_runtime_error(CATCH_MAKE_MSG( __VA_ARGS__ ))
8655
8656#define CATCH_ENFORCE( condition, ... ) \
8657 do{ if( !(condition) ) CATCH_ERROR( __VA_ARGS__ ); } while(false)

8741#include <cassert>
8742
8743namespace Catch {
8744
8755 class FatalConditionHandler {
8756 bool m_started = false;
8757
8758 // Install/disengage implementation for specific platform.
8759 // Should be if-defed to work on current platform, can assume
8760 // engage-disengage 1:1 pairing.
8761 void engage_platform();
8762 void disengage_platform() noexcept;
8763 public:
8764 // Should also have platform-specific implementations as needed
8765 FatalConditionHandler();
8766 ~FatalConditionHandler();
8767
8768 void engage() {
8769 assert(!m_started && "Handler cannot be installed twice.");
8770 m_started = true;
8771 engage_platform();
8772 }
8773
8774 void disengage() noexcept {
8775 assert(m_started && "Handler cannot be uninstalled without being installed first");
8776 m_started = false;
8777 disengage_platform();
8778 }
8779 };
8780
8782 class FatalConditionHandlerGuard {
8783 FatalConditionHandler* m_handler;
8784 public:
8785 FatalConditionHandlerGuard(FatalConditionHandler* handler):
8786 m_handler(handler) {
8787 m_handler->engage();
8788 }
8789 ~FatalConditionHandlerGuard() {
8790 m_handler->disengage();
8791 }
8792 };
8793
8794} // end namespace Catch

8804#ifndef CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
8805#define CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
8806
8807namespace Catch {

8809 bool isnan(double d);
8810}
8811
8812#endif // CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
8813
8814#include <cassert>
8815#include <cmath>
8816#include <cstdint>
8817#include <utility>
8818#include <limits>
8819
8820namespace Catch {
8821 namespace Detail {
8822
8823 uint32_t convertToBits(float f);
8824 uint64_t convertToBits(double d);
8825
8826 } // end namespace Detail
8827
8828
8829
8830#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8831# pragma GCC diagnostic push
8832 // We do a bunch of direct compensations of floating point numbers,
8833 // because we know what we are doing and actually do want the direct
8834 // comparison behaviour.
8835# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
8836#endif
8837
8855 template <typename FP>
8856 uint64_t ulpDistance( FP lhs, FP rhs ) {
8857 assert( std::numeric_limits<FP>::is_iec559 &&
8858 "ulpDistance assumes IEEE-754 format for floating point types" );
8859 assert( !Catch::isnan( lhs ) &&
8860 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
8861 assert( !Catch::isnan( rhs ) &&
8862 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
8863
8864 // We want X == Y to imply 0 ULP distance even if X and Y aren't
8865 // bit-equal (-0 and 0), or X - Y != 0 (same sign infinities).
8866 if ( lhs == rhs ) { return 0; }
8867
8868 // We need a properly typed positive zero for type inference.
8869 static constexpr FP positive_zero{};
8870
8871 // We want to ensure that +/- 0 is always represented as positive zero
8872 if ( lhs == positive_zero ) { lhs = positive_zero; }
8873 if ( rhs == positive_zero ) { rhs = positive_zero; }
8874
8875 // If arguments have different signs, we can handle them by summing
8876 // how far are they from 0 each.
8877 if ( std::signbit( lhs ) != std::signbit( rhs ) ) {
8878 return ulpDistance( std::abs( lhs ), positive_zero ) +
8879 ulpDistance( std::abs( rhs ), positive_zero );
8880 }
8881
8882 // When both lhs and rhs are of the same sign, we can just
8883 // read the numbers bitwise as integers, and then subtract them
8884 // (assuming IEEE).
8885 uint64_t lc = Detail::convertToBits( lhs );
8886 uint64_t rc = Detail::convertToBits( rhs );
8887
8888 // The ulp distance between two numbers is symmetric, so to avoid
8889 // dealing with overflows we want the bigger converted number on the lhs
8890 if ( lc < rc ) {
8891 std::swap( lc, rc );
8892 }
8893
8894 return lc - rc;
8895 }
8896
8897#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8898# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
8899#endif
8900
8901
8902} // end namespace Catch
8903
8904#endif // CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
8905

9196 struct NameAndLocation {
9197 std::string name;
9198 SourceLineInfo location;
9199
9200 NameAndLocation( std::string&& _name, SourceLineInfo const& _location );
9201 friend bool operator==(NameAndLocation const& lhs, NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
9202 return lhs.name == rhs.name
9203 && lhs.location == rhs.location;
9204 }
9205 friend bool operator!=(NameAndLocation const& lhs,
9206 NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
9207 return !( lhs == rhs );
9208 }
9209 };
9210
9218 struct NameAndLocationRef {
9219 StringRef name;
9220 SourceLineInfo location;
9221
9222 constexpr NameAndLocationRef( StringRef name_,
9223 SourceLineInfo location_ ):
9224 name( name_ ), location( location_ ) {}
9225
9226 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocation const& lhs,
9227 NameAndLocationRef rhs ) {
9228 return StringRef( lhs.name ) == rhs.name &&
9229 lhs.location == rhs.location;
9230 }
9231 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocationRef lhs,
9232 NameAndLocation const& rhs ) {
9233 return rhs == lhs;
9234 }
9235 };
9236
9237 class ITracker;
9238

9252 CompletedSuccessfully,
9253 Failed
9254 };
9255
9256 ITracker* m_parent = nullptr;
9257 Children m_children;
9258 CycleState m_runState = NotStarted;
9259
9260 public:
9261 ITracker( NameAndLocation&& nameAndLoc, ITracker* parent ):
9262 m_nameAndLocation( CATCH_MOVE(nameAndLoc) ),
9263 m_parent( parent )
9264 {}
9265
9266

9269 return m_nameAndLocation;
9270 }

9272 return m_parent;
9273 }

9288

9291 virtual void fail() = 0;
9292 void markAsNeedingAnotherRun();
9293
9295 void addChild( ITrackerPtr&& child );
9301 ITracker* findChild( NameAndLocationRef nameAndLocation );

9304 return !m_children.empty();
9305 }
9306

9310
9317 virtual bool isSectionTracker() const;
9324 virtual bool isGeneratorTracker() const;
9325 };

9522 Totals m_totals;
9523 IEventListenerPtr m_reporter;
9524 std::vector<MessageInfo> m_messages;
9525 std::vector<ScopedMessage> m_messageScopes; /* Keeps owners of so-called unscoped messages. */
9526 AssertionInfo m_lastAssertionInfo;
9527 std::vector<SectionEndInfo> m_unfinishedSections;
9528 std::vector<ITracker*> m_activeSections;
9529 TrackerContext m_trackerContext;
9530 FatalConditionHandler m_fatalConditionhandler;
9531 bool m_lastAssertionPassed = false;
9532 bool m_shouldReportUnexpected = true;
9533 bool m_includeSuccessfulResults;
9534 };

9543#ifndef CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
9544#define CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
9545
9546
9547#include <cmath>
9548#include <algorithm>
9549
9550namespace Catch {
9551
9552 template<typename Container>
9553 Container createShard(Container const& container, std::size_t const shardCount, std::size_t const shardIndex) {
9554 assert(shardCount > shardIndex);
9555
9556 if (shardCount == 1) {
9557 return container;
9558 }
9559
9560 const std::size_t totalTestCount = container.size();
9561
9562 const std::size_t shardSize = totalTestCount / shardCount;
9563 const std::size_t leftoverTests = totalTestCount % shardCount;
9564
9565 const std::size_t startIndex = shardIndex * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex, leftoverTests);
9566 const std::size_t endIndex = (shardIndex + 1) * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex + 1, leftoverTests);
9567
9568 auto startIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(startIndex));
9569 auto endIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(endIndex));
9570
9571 return Container(startIterator, endIterator);
9572 }
9573
9574}
9575
9576#endif // CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED

9580#define CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED
9581
9582namespace Catch {
9583
9584 struct ISingleton {
9585 virtual ~ISingleton(); // = default
9586 };
9587
9588
9589 void addSingleton( ISingleton* singleton );
9590 void cleanupSingletons();
9591
9592
9593 template<typename SingletonImplT, typename InterfaceT = SingletonImplT, typename MutableInterfaceT = InterfaceT>
9594 class Singleton : SingletonImplT, public ISingleton {
9595
9596 static auto getInternal() -> Singleton* {
9597 static Singleton* s_instance = nullptr;
9598 if( !s_instance ) {
9599 s_instance = new Singleton;
9600 addSingleton( s_instance );
9601 }
9602 return s_instance;
9603 }
9604
9605 public:
9606 static auto get() -> InterfaceT const& {
9607 return *getInternal();
9608 }
9609 static auto getMutable() -> MutableInterfaceT& {
9610 return *getInternal();
9611 }
9612 };
9613
9614} // namespace Catch

9924 class Column {
9925 // String to be written out
9926 std::string m_string;
9927 // Width of the column for linebreaking
9928 size_t m_width = CATCH_CONFIG_CONSOLE_WIDTH - 1;
9929 // Indentation of other lines (including first if initial indent is unset)
9930 size_t m_indent = 0;
9931 // Indentation of the first line
9932 size_t m_initialIndent = std::string::npos;
9933
9934 public:
9938 class const_iterator {
9939 friend Column;
9940 struct EndTag {};
9941
9942 Column const& m_column;
9943 // Where does the current line start?
9944 size_t m_lineStart = 0;
9945 // How long should the current line be?
9946 size_t m_lineLength = 0;
9947 // How far have we checked the string to iterate?
9948 size_t m_parsedTo = 0;
9949 // Should a '-' be appended to the line?
9950 bool m_addHyphen = false;
9951
9952 const_iterator( Column const& column, EndTag ):
9953 m_column( column ), m_lineStart( m_column.m_string.size() ) {}
9954
9955 // Calculates the length of the current line
9956 void calcLength();
9957
9958 // Returns current indention width
9959 size_t indentSize() const;
9960
9961 // Creates an indented and (optionally) suffixed string from
9962 // current iterator position, indentation and length.
9963 std::string addIndentAndSuffix( size_t position,
9964 size_t length ) const;
9965
9966 public:
9967 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
9968 using value_type = std::string;
9969 using pointer = value_type*;
9970 using reference = value_type&;
9971 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
9972
9973 explicit const_iterator( Column const& column );
9974
9975 std::string operator*() const;
9976
9977 const_iterator& operator++();
9978 const_iterator operator++( int );
9979
9980 bool operator==( const_iterator const& other ) const {
9981 return m_lineStart == other.m_lineStart && &m_column == &other.m_column;
9982 }
9983 bool operator!=( const_iterator const& other ) const {
9984 return !operator==( other );
9985 }
9986 };
9987 using iterator = const_iterator;
9988
9989 explicit Column( std::string const& text ): m_string( text ) {}
9990
9991 Column& width( size_t newWidth ) {
9992 assert( newWidth > 0 );
9993 m_width = newWidth;
9994 return *this;
9995 }
9996 Column& indent( size_t newIndent ) {
9997 m_indent = newIndent;
9998 return *this;
9999 }
10000 Column& initialIndent( size_t newIndent ) {
10001 m_initialIndent = newIndent;
10002 return *this;
10003 }
10004
10005 size_t width() const { return m_width; }
10006 const_iterator begin() const { return const_iterator( *this ); }
10007 const_iterator end() const { return { *this, const_iterator::EndTag{} }; }
10008
10009 friend std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream& os,
10010 Column const& col );
10011
10012 Columns operator+( Column const& other );
10013 };
10014
10016 Column Spacer( size_t spaceWidth );

10028 size_t m_activeIterators;

10036 using reference = value_type&;

10045 return m_iterators != other.m_iterators;
10046 }

10048 iterator& operator++();
10049 iterator operator++( int );
10050 };
10051 using const_iterator = iterator;
10052
10053 iterator begin() const { return iterator( *this ); }
10054 iterator end() const { return { *this, iterator::EndTag() }; }
10055
10056 Columns& operator+=( Column const& col );

10157 template <typename T,
10158 // Without this SFINAE, this overload is a better match
10159 // for `std::string`, `char const*`, `char const[N]` args.
10160 // While it would still work, it would cause code bloat
10161 // and multiple iteration over the strings

10199 // Without this SFINAE, this overload is a better match
10200 // for `std::string`, `char const*`, `char const[N]` args.
10201 // While it would still work, it would cause code bloat
10202 // and multiple iteration over the strings
10203 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
10204 !std::is_convertible<T, StringRef>::value>>
10205 XmlWriter& writeAttribute( StringRef name, T const& attribute ) {
10206 ReusableStringStream rss;
10207 rss << attribute;
10208 return writeAttribute( name, rss.str() );
10209 }

10270
10271namespace Catch {
10272
10273 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
10274 class MatchExpr : public ITransientExpression {
10275 ArgT && m_arg;
10276 MatcherT const& m_matcher;
10277 public:
10278 MatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher )
10279 : ITransientExpression{ true, matcher.match( arg ) }, // not forwarding arg here on purpose
10280 m_arg( CATCH_FORWARD(arg) ),
10281 m_matcher( matcher )
10282 {}
10283
10284 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream& os ) const override {
10285 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_arg )
10286 << ' '
10287 << m_matcher.toString();
10288 }
10289 };
10290
10291 namespace Matchers {
10292 template <typename ArgT>
10293 class MatcherBase;
10294 }
10295
10296 using StringMatcher = Matchers::MatcherBase<std::string>;
10297
10298 void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, StringMatcher const& matcher );
10299
10300 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
10301 auto makeMatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher ) -> MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT> {
10302 return MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT>( CATCH_FORWARD(arg), matcher );
10303 }
10304
10305} // namespace Catch
10306
10307
10309#define INTERNAL_CHECK_THAT( macroName, matcher, resultDisposition, arg ) \
10310 do { \
10311 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(arg) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
10312 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
10313 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( arg, matcher ) ); \
10314 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10315 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10316 } while( false )
10317
10318
10320#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_MATCHES( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
10321 do { \
10322 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
10323 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
10324 try { \
10325 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__ ); \
10326 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
10327 } \
10328 catch( exceptionType const& ex ) { \
10329 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( ex, matcher ) ); \
10330 } \
10331 catch( ... ) { \
10332 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
10333 } \
10334 else \
10335 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
10336 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10337 } while( false )
10338
10339
10340#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_IMPL_HPP_INCLUDED

10353 MatcherUntypedBase(MatcherUntypedBase&&) = default;

10359

10364 };

10367 template<typename T>
10368 class MatcherBase : public MatcherUntypedBase {
10369 public:
10370 virtual bool match( T const& arg ) const = 0;
10371 };

10374
10375 template<typename ArgT>
10376 class MatchAllOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10377 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
10378
10379 public:
10380 MatchAllOf() = default;
10381 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
10382 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
10383 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
10384 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
10385
10386
10387 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10388 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10389 if (!matcher->match(arg))
10390 return false;
10391 }
10392 return true;
10393 }
10394 std::string describe() const override {
10395 std::string description;
10396 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
10397 description += "( ";
10398 bool first = true;
10399 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10400 if( first )
10401 first = false;
10402 else
10403 description += " and ";
10404 description += matcher->toString();
10405 }
10406 description += " )";
10407 return description;
10408 }
10409
10410 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatchAllOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
10411 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
10412 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
10413 }
10414 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf&& rhs) {
10415 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
10416 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
10417 }
10418 };
10419
10422 template<typename ArgT>
10423 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10426 template<typename ArgT>
10427 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10428
10429 template<typename ArgT>
10430 class MatchAnyOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10431 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
10432 public:
10433 MatchAnyOf() = default;
10434 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
10435 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
10436 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
10437 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
10438
10439 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10440 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10441 if (matcher->match(arg))
10442 return true;
10443 }
10444 return false;
10445 }
10446 std::string describe() const override {
10447 std::string description;
10448 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
10449 description += "( ";
10450 bool first = true;
10451 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10452 if( first )
10453 first = false;
10454 else
10455 description += " or ";
10456 description += matcher->toString();
10457 }
10458 description += " )";
10459 return description;
10460 }
10461
10462 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatchAnyOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
10463 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
10464 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
10465 }
10466 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf&& rhs) {
10467 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
10468 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
10469 }
10470 };
10471
10474 template<typename ArgT>
10475 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10478 template<typename ArgT>
10479 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10480
10481 template<typename ArgT>
10482 class MatchNotOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10483 MatcherBase<ArgT> const& m_underlyingMatcher;
10484
10485 public:
10486 explicit MatchNotOf( MatcherBase<ArgT> const& underlyingMatcher ):
10487 m_underlyingMatcher( underlyingMatcher )
10488 {}
10489
10490 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10491 return !m_underlyingMatcher.match( arg );
10492 }
10493
10494 std::string describe() const override {
10495 return "not " + m_underlyingMatcher.toString();
10496 }
10497 };
10498
10499 } // namespace Detail

10501 template <typename T>
10502 Detail::MatchAllOf<T> operator&& (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
10503 return Detail::MatchAllOf<T>{} && lhs && rhs;
10504 }
10505 template <typename T>
10506 Detail::MatchAnyOf<T> operator|| (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
10507 return Detail::MatchAnyOf<T>{} || lhs || rhs;
10508 }
10509
10510 template <typename T>
10511 Detail::MatchNotOf<T> operator! (MatcherBase<T> const& matcher) {
10512 return Detail::MatchNotOf<T>{ matcher };
10513 }

10598 template<std::size_t N, std::size_t M>
10599 std::array<void const*, N + M> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, std::array<void const*, M> && rhs) {
10600 std::array<void const*, N + M> arr{};
10601 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
10602 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), M, arr.begin() + N);
10603 return arr;
10604 }
10605
10606 template<std::size_t N>
10607 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, void const* rhs) {
10608 std::array<void const*, N+1> arr{};
10609 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
10610 arr[N] = rhs;
10611 return arr;
10612 }
10613
10614 template<std::size_t N>
10615 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(void const* lhs, std::array<void const*, N> && rhs) {
10616 std::array<void const*, N + 1> arr{ {lhs} };
10617 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), N, arr.begin() + 1);
10618 return arr;
10619 }
