10621 template<typename T>
10622 using is_generic_matcher = std::is_base_of<
10623 Catch::Matchers::MatcherGenericBase,
10624 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
10625 >;
10626
10627 template<typename... Ts>
10628 using are_generic_matchers = Catch::Detail::conjunction<is_generic_matcher<Ts>...>;
10629
10630 template<typename T>
10631 using is_matcher = std::is_base_of<
10632 Catch::Matchers::MatcherUntypedBase,
10633 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
10634 >;
10635
10636
10637 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
10638 bool match_all_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
10639 return true;
10640 }
10641
10642 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
10643 bool match_all_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
10644 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) && match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
10645 }
10646
10647
10648 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
10649 bool match_any_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
10650 return false;
10651 }
10652
10653 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
10654 bool match_any_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
10655 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) || match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
10656 }
10657
10658 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::string const* descriptions_begin, std::string const* descriptions_end);
10659
10660 template<typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t... Idx>
10661 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx...>) {
10662 std::array<std::string, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> descriptions {{
10663 static_cast<MatcherTs const*>(matchers[Idx])->toString()...
10664 }};
10665
10666 return describe_multi_matcher(combine, descriptions.data(), descriptions.data() + descriptions.size());
10667 }

10670 template<typename... MatcherTs>
10671 class MatchAllOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
10672 public:
10673 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
10674 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
10675 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
10676 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
10677
10678 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
10679 explicit MatchAllOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
10680
10681 template<typename Arg>
10682 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
10683 return match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
10684 }
10685
10686 std::string describe() const override {
10687 return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" and "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
10688 }
10689
10690 // Has to be public to enable the concatenating operators
10691 // below, because they are not friend of the RHS, only LHS,
10692 // and thus cannot access private fields of RHS
10693 std::array<void const*, sizeof...( MatcherTs )> m_matchers;
10694
10695
10697 template<typename... MatchersRHS>
10698 friend
10699 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator && (
10700 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
10701 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
10702 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
10703 }
10704
10706 template<typename MatcherRHS>
10707 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value,
10708 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator && (
10709 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
10710 MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
10711 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(&rhs))};
10712 }
10713
10715 template<typename MatcherLHS>
10716 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value,
10717 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator && (
10718 MatcherLHS const& lhs,
10719 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
10720 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
10721 }
10722 };

10809 template<typename MatcherLHS, typename MatcherRHS>
10810 std::enable_if_t<Detail::are_generic_matchers<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>::value, Detail::MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>>
10811 operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
10812 return { lhs, rhs };
10813 }
10814

10817 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
10818 return { lhs, rhs };
10819 }
10820
10822 template<typename MatcherT>
10823 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherT>::value, Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>>
10824 operator ! (MatcherT const& matcher) {
10825 return Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>{matcher};
10826 }

10832 operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {
10833 return { lhs, rhs };
10834 }

10838 operator && (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
10839 return { lhs, rhs };
10840 }

10844 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {

10850 operator || (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {

10882 {}
10883
10884 template <typename RangeLike>
10885 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
10886#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
10887 using Catch::Detail::size;
10888#else
10889 using std::size;
10890#endif
10891 return size(rng) == m_target_size;
10892 }
10893
10894 std::string describe() const override;
10895 };
10896
10897 template <typename Matcher>
10898 class SizeMatchesMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
10899 Matcher m_matcher;
10900 public:
10901 explicit SizeMatchesMatcher(Matcher m):
10902 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(m))
10903 {}
10904
10905 template <typename RangeLike>
10906 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
10907#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
10908 using Catch::Detail::size;
10909#else
10910 using std::size;
10911#endif
10912 return m_matcher.match(size(rng));
10913 }
10914
10915 std::string describe() const override {
10916 return "size matches " + m_matcher.describe();
10917 }
10918 };
10919
10920
10922 IsEmptyMatcher IsEmpty();
10924 HasSizeMatcher SizeIs(std::size_t sz);
10925 template <typename Matcher>
10926 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher<Matcher>::value,
10927 SizeMatchesMatcher<Matcher>> SizeIs(Matcher&& m) {
10928 return SizeMatchesMatcher<Matcher>{CATCH_FORWARD(m)};
10929 }

10944namespace Catch {
10945 namespace Matchers {
10947 template <typename T, typename Equality>
10948 class ContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
10949 T m_desired;
10950 Equality m_eq;
10951 public:
10952 template <typename T2, typename Equality2>
10953 ContainsElementMatcher(T2&& target, Equality2&& predicate):
10954 m_desired(CATCH_FORWARD(target)),
10955 m_eq(CATCH_FORWARD(predicate))
10956 {}
10957
10958 std::string describe() const override {
10959 return "contains element " + Catch::Detail::stringify(m_desired);
10960 }
10961
10962 template <typename RangeLike>
10963 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
10964 using std::begin; using std::end;
10965
10966 return end(rng) != std::find_if(begin(rng), end(rng),
10967 [&](auto const& elem) {
10968 return m_eq(elem, m_desired);
10969 });
10970 }
10971 };
10972
10974 template <typename Matcher>
10975 class ContainsMatcherMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
10976 Matcher m_matcher;
10977 public:
10978 // Note that we do a copy+move to avoid having to SFINAE this
10979 // constructor (and also avoid some perfect forwarding failure
10980 // cases)
10981 ContainsMatcherMatcher(Matcher matcher):
10982 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(matcher))
10983 {}
10984
10985 template <typename RangeLike>
10986 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
10987 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
10988 if (m_matcher.match(elem)) {
10989 return true;
10990 }
10991 }
10992 return false;
10993 }
10994
10995 std::string describe() const override {
10996 return "contains element matching " + m_matcher.describe();
10997 }
10998 };
10999
11005 template <typename T>

11007 ContainsElementMatcher<T, std::equal_to<>>> Contains(T&& elem) {
11008 return { CATCH_FORWARD(elem), std::equal_to<>{} };
11009 }

11013 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher<Matcher>::value,
11014 ContainsMatcherMatcher<Matcher>> Contains(Matcher&& matcher) {
11015 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
11016 }
11017
11023 template <typename T, typename Equality>
11024 ContainsElementMatcher<T, Equality> Contains(T&& elem, Equality&& eq) {

11026 }

11100 class WithinAbsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<double> {
11101 public:
11102 WithinAbsMatcher(double target, double margin);

11104 std::string describe() const override;
11105 private:
11106 double m_target;

11109
11110 class WithinUlpsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<double> {
11111 public:
11112 WithinUlpsMatcher( double target,
11113 uint64_t ulps,
11114 Detail::FloatingPointKind baseType );
11115 bool match(double const& matchee) const override;
11116 std::string describe() const override;
11117 private:
11118 double m_target;
11119 uint64_t m_ulps;
11120 Detail::FloatingPointKind m_type;
11121 };
11122
11123 // Given IEEE-754 format for floats and doubles, we can assume
11124 // that float -> double promotion is lossless. Given this, we can
11125 // assume that if we do the standard relative comparison of
11126 // |lhs - rhs| <= epsilon * max(fabs(lhs), fabs(rhs)), then we get
11127 // the same result if we do this for floats, as if we do this for
11128 // doubles that were promoted from floats.
11129 class WithinRelMatcher final : public MatcherBase<double> {
11130 public:
11131 WithinRelMatcher( double target, double epsilon );
11132 bool match(double const& matchee) const override;
11133 std::string describe() const override;
11134 private:
11135 double m_target;
11136 double m_epsilon;
11137 };
11138
11140 WithinUlpsMatcher WithinULP(double target, uint64_t maxUlpDiff);
11142 WithinUlpsMatcher WithinULP(float target, uint64_t maxUlpDiff);
11144 WithinAbsMatcher WithinAbs(double target, double margin);
11145
11147 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target, double eps);
11149 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target);
11151 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target, float eps);
11153 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target);
11154
11155} // namespace Matchers

11174template <typename T, typename Predicate>
11175class PredicateMatcher final : public MatcherBase<T> {
11176 Predicate m_predicate;
11177 std::string m_description;
11178public:
11179
11180 PredicateMatcher(Predicate&& elem, std::string const& descr)
11181 :m_predicate(CATCH_FORWARD(elem)),
11182 m_description(Detail::finalizeDescription(descr))
11183 {}
11184
11185 bool match( T const& item ) const override {
11186 return m_predicate(item);
11187 }
11188
11189 std::string describe() const override {
11190 return m_description;
11191 }
11192};
11193
11199 template<typename T, typename Pred>
11200 PredicateMatcher<T, Pred> Predicate(Pred&& predicate, std::string const& description = "") {
11201 static_assert(is_callable<Pred(T)>::value, "Predicate not callable with argument T");
11202 static_assert(std::is_same<bool, FunctionReturnType<Pred, T>>::value, "Predicate does not return bool");
11203 return PredicateMatcher<T, Pred>(CATCH_FORWARD(predicate), description);
11204 }

11383 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
11384 class RangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11385 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
11386 Equality m_predicate;
11387
11388 public:
11389 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
11390 RangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
11391 Equality2&& predicate ):
11392 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
11393 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
11394
11395 template <typename RangeLike>
11396 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
11397 using std::begin;
11398 using std::end;
11399 return std::equal( begin(m_desired),
11400 end(m_desired),
11401 begin(rng),
11402 end(rng),
11403 m_predicate );
11404 }
11405
11406 std::string describe() const override {
11407 return "elements are " + Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
11408 }
11409 };
11410
11415 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
11416 class UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11417 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
11418 Equality m_predicate;
11419
11420 public:
11421 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
11422 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
11423 Equality2&& predicate ):
11424 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
11425 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
11426
11427 template <typename RangeLike>
11428 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
11429 using std::begin;
11430 using std::end;
11431 return std::is_permutation( begin( m_desired ),
11432 end( m_desired ),
11433 begin( rng ),
11434 end( rng ),
11435 m_predicate );
11436 }
11437
11438 std::string describe() const override {
11439 return "unordered elements are " +
11440 ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
11441 }
11442 };
11443

11454 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), std::equal_to<>{} };
11455 }

11586 template<typename T, typename Alloc>
11587 class VectorContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, Alloc>> {
11588 T const& m_comparator;
11589
11590 public:
11591 VectorContainsElementMatcher(T const& comparator):
11592 m_comparator(comparator)
11593 {}
11594
11595 bool match(std::vector<T, Alloc> const& v) const override {
11596 for (auto const& el : v) {
11597 if (el == m_comparator) {
11598 return true;
11599 }
11600 }
11601 return false;
11602 }
11603
11604 std::string describe() const override {
11605 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
11606 }
11607 };
11608
11609 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
11610 class ContainsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
11611 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
11612
11613 public:
11614 ContainsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
11615 m_comparator( comparator )
11616 {}
11617
11618 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
11619 // !TBD: see note in EqualsMatcher
11620 if (m_comparator.size() > v.size())
11621 return false;
11622 for (auto const& comparator : m_comparator) {
11623 auto present = false;
11624 for (const auto& el : v) {
11625 if (el == comparator) {
11626 present = true;
11627 break;
11628 }
11629 }
11630 if (!present) {
11631 return false;
11632 }
11633 }
11634 return true;
11635 }
11636 std::string describe() const override {
11637 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
11638 }
11639 };
11640
11641 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
11642 class EqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
11643 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
11644
11645 public:
11646 EqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
11647 m_comparator( comparator )
11648 {}
11649
11650 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
11651 // !TBD: This currently works if all elements can be compared using !=
11652 // - a more general approach would be via a compare template that defaults
11653 // to using !=. but could be specialised for, e.g. std::vector<T> etc
11654 // - then just call that directly
11655 if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
11656 return false;
11657 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
11658 if (m_comparator[i] != v[i])
11659 return false;
11660 return true;
11661 }
11662 std::string describe() const override {
11663 return "Equals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
11664 }
11665 };
11666
11667 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
11668 class ApproxMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
11669 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
11670 mutable Catch::Approx approx = Catch::Approx::custom();
11671
11672 public:
11673 ApproxMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
11674 m_comparator( comparator )
11675 {}
11676
11677 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
11678 if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
11679 return false;
11680 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
11681 if (m_comparator[i] != approx(v[i]))
11682 return false;
11683 return true;
11684 }
11685 std::string describe() const override {
11686 return "is approx: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
11687 }
11688 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
11689 ApproxMatcher& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
11690 approx.epsilon(static_cast<double>(newEpsilon));
11691 return *this;
11692 }
11693 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
11694 ApproxMatcher& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
11695 approx.margin(static_cast<double>(newMargin));
11696 return *this;
11697 }
11698 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
11699 ApproxMatcher& scale( T const& newScale ) {
11700 approx.scale(static_cast<double>(newScale));
11701 return *this;
11702 }
11703 };
11704
11705 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
11706 class UnorderedEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
11707 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_target;
11708
11709 public:
11710 UnorderedEqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target):
11711 m_target(target)
11712 {}
11713 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& vec) const override {
11714 if (m_target.size() != vec.size()) {
11715 return false;
11716 }
11717 return std::is_permutation(m_target.begin(), m_target.end(), vec.begin());
11718 }
11719
11720 std::string describe() const override {
11721 return "UnorderedEquals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify(m_target);
11722 }
11723 };
11724
11725
11726 // The following functions create the actual matcher objects.
11727 // This allows the types to be inferred
11728
11730 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
11731 ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Contains( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
11732 return ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
11733 }
11734
11736 template<typename T, typename Alloc = std::allocator<T>>
11737 VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc> VectorContains( T const& comparator ) {
11738 return VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc>(comparator);
11739 }
11740
11742 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
11743 EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Equals( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
11744 return EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
11745 }
11746
11748 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
11749 ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Approx( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
11750 return ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
11751 }
11752
11754 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
11755 UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> UnorderedEquals(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target) {
11756 return UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(target);
11757 }
11758
11759} // namespace Matchers
11760} // namespace Catch
11761
11762#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_VECTOR_HPP_INCLUDED
11763
11764#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_ALL_HPP_INCLUDED

12098 class CumulativeReporterBase : public ReporterBase {
12099 public:
12100 template<typename T, typename ChildNodeT>
12101 struct Node {
12102 explicit Node( T const& _value ) : value( _value ) {}
12103
12104 using ChildNodes = std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<ChildNodeT>>;
12105 T value;
12106 ChildNodes children;
12107 };
12108 struct SectionNode {
12109 explicit SectionNode(SectionStats const& _stats) : stats(_stats) {}
12110
12111 bool operator == (SectionNode const& other) const {
12112 return stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo == other.stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo;
12113 }
12114
12115 bool hasAnyAssertions() const;
12116
12117 SectionStats stats;
12118 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode>> childSections;
12119 std::vector<Detail::AssertionOrBenchmarkResult> assertionsAndBenchmarks;
12120 std::string stdOut;
12121 std::string stdErr;
12122 };
12123
12124
12125 using TestCaseNode = Node<TestCaseStats, SectionNode>;
12126 using TestRunNode = Node<TestRunStats, TestCaseNode>;
12127
12128 // GCC5 compat: we cannot use inherited constructor, because it
12129 // doesn't implement backport of P0136
12130 CumulativeReporterBase(ReporterConfig&& _config):
12131 ReporterBase(CATCH_MOVE(_config))
12132 {}
12133 ~CumulativeReporterBase() override;
12134
12135 void benchmarkPreparing( StringRef ) override {}
12136 void benchmarkStarting( BenchmarkInfo const& ) override {}
12137 void benchmarkEnded( BenchmarkStats<> const& benchmarkStats ) override;
12138 void benchmarkFailed( StringRef ) override {}
12139
12140 void noMatchingTestCases( StringRef ) override {}
12141 void reportInvalidTestSpec( StringRef ) override {}
12142 void fatalErrorEncountered( StringRef /*error*/ ) override {}
12143
12144 void testRunStarting( TestRunInfo const& ) override {}
12145
12146 void testCaseStarting( TestCaseInfo const& ) override {}
12147 void testCasePartialStarting( TestCaseInfo const&, uint64_t ) override {}
12148 void sectionStarting( SectionInfo const& sectionInfo ) override;
12149
12150 void assertionStarting( AssertionInfo const& ) override {}
12151
12152 void assertionEnded( AssertionStats const& assertionStats ) override;
12153 void sectionEnded( SectionStats const& sectionStats ) override;
12154 void testCasePartialEnded( TestCaseStats const&, uint64_t ) override {}
12155 void testCaseEnded( TestCaseStats const& testCaseStats ) override;
12156 void testRunEnded( TestRunStats const& testRunStats ) override;
12158 virtual void testRunEndedCumulative() = 0;
12159
12160 void skipTest(TestCaseInfo const&) override {}
12161
12162 protected:
12164 bool m_shouldStoreSuccesfulAssertions = true;
12166 bool m_shouldStoreFailedAssertions = true;
12167
12168 // We need lazy construction here. We should probably refactor it
12169 // later, after the events are redone.
12171 Detail::unique_ptr<TestRunNode> m_testRun;
12172
12173 private:
12174 // Note: We rely on pointer identity being stable, which is why
12175 // we store pointers to the nodes rather than the values.
12176 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<TestCaseNode>> m_testCases;
12177 // Root section of the _current_ test case
12178 Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode> m_rootSection;
12179 // Deepest section of the _current_ test case
12180 SectionNode* m_deepestSection = nullptr;
12181 // Stack of _active_ sections in the _current_ test case
12182 std::vector<SectionNode*> m_sectionStack;
12183 };
12184
12185} // end namespace Catch

12501 class TypedListenerFactory : public EventListenerFactory {

12505 return T::getDescription();
12506 }

12509 return "(No description provided)";
12510 }

12514 m_listenerName( listenerName ) {}

12518 }
12519
12520 StringRef getName() const override {
12521 return m_listenerName;
12522 }
12523
12524 std::string getDescription() const override {
12525 return getDescriptionImpl( Detail::has_description<T>{} );
12526 }
12527 };
12528
12529 public:
12530 ListenerRegistrar(StringRef listenerName) {
12531 getMutableRegistryHub().registerListener( Detail::make_unique<TypedListenerFactory>(listenerName) );
12532 }
12533 };
12534}

12543 catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( name ); \
12544 } \
12545 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION

12548 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \

12551 Catch::ListenerRegistrar<listenerType> INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( \
12552 catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( #listenerType ); \
12553 } \
12554 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
12555
